        HELP_SELLISTE_NOT_INTERESTED_MY_PLEASURE                                = 10423,  -- Help Selliste? Not interested. My pleasure!
        HMPH_ANOTHER_SYNERGIST_TOO_PREOCCUPIED_WITH_HIS_HER                     = 10424,  -- Hmph! Another synergist too preoccupied with his/her] own oh-so-important research to share his/her] knowledge with the common folk. But hey, I'm a patient woman. If you ever have a change of heart, I'll be here!
        WONDERFUL_WHO_SAID_THAT_ALL_SYNERGISTS_WERE_SNOOTY                      = 10425,  -- Wonderful! Who said that all synergists were snooty, good-for-nothing snobs? Not me, that's for sure!
        ANYHOW_ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN_YOU_MAY_HAVE                                 = 10426,  -- Anyhow, allow me to explain. You may have noticed that these synergy furnaces are a tad unwieldy, to say the least.
        NOT_MUCH_OF_A_CONCERN_WHEN_YOU_RE                                       = 10427,  -- Not much of a concern when you're synergizing here in the city, but hardly suited to the peripatetic life of an adventurer. That's when it hit me!
        SURELY_YOU_VE_READ_THE_HISTORIES_IN_THE                                 = 10428,  -- Surely you've read the histories. In the days of the Crystal War, there were those studious types who could make massive tomes appear and disappear out of thin air. What were they called again...? Bookheads? Eggworms?
        BUT_IT_S_NOT_THEIR_NAME_THAT_S                                          = 10429,  -- But it's not their name that's important. No, it's the technique they used to store and summon their libraries! "Arcane snap" or something like that? Anyway!
        SO_I_FIGURE_IF_ONLY_I_COULD_GET                                         = 10430,  -- So I figure, if only I could get my hands on some of the astral whatchamacallit that the egghead-types used to whip out their grim-whatsits, I could toss together a nifty gizmo that could work the same magic for these synergy thingamajigs!
        I_TELL_YOU_SOMETIMES_I_AMAZE_EVEN_MYSELF                                = 10431,  -- I tell you, sometimes I amaze even myself with the clarity of my ideas!
        BUT_YOU_LOOK_PUZZLED_SORRY_LET_S_TRY                                    = 10432,  -- But you look puzzled. Sorry, let's try that again in layman's terms.
        I_M_WORKING_ON_A_TOTALLY_AMAZING_INVENTION                              = 10433,  -- I'm working on a totally amazing invention, and you're going to help me complete it!
        ALL_YOU_NEED_TO_DO_IS_USE_YOUR                                          = 10434,  -- All you need to do is use your synergy skills to whip up %, and I'll take care of the rest. Nothing could be easier! So, what do you say?
        HELP_SELLISTE_NOT_INTERESTED_MY_PLEASURE_2                              = 10435,  -- Help Selliste? Not interested. My pleasure!
        SPLENDID_YOU_LL_BE_WANTING_TO_KNOW_THE                                  = 10436,  -- Splendid! You'll be wanting to know the recipe then, won't you? Why, it's simple enough.
        IT_S_JUST                                                               = 10437,  -- It's just %, %, %, %, %...
        AND_FINALLY_TOSS_THEM_ALL_INTO_ONE_OF                                   = 10438,  -- ...And finally, %. Toss them all into one of those furnace doodads, work your synergy magic on it, trade the product back here to me, and we're in business!
        I_SUSPECT_YOU_CAN_FIND_THE_INGREDIENTS_SOMEWHERE                        = 10439,  -- I suspect you can find the ingredients somewhere strong in elemental energy. Maybe a place with some of those big crystal doohickeys lying around?
        BUT_YOU_RE_THE_ADVENTURER_I_HAVE_BIGGER                                 = 10440,  -- But you're the adventurer. I have bigger flasques to fulminate! Good luck out there!
        I_KNEW_YOU_D_BE_BACK_HOW_ABOUT                                          = 10441,  -- I knew you'd be back! How about it? Ready to do the world a favor and help me complete my most marvelous invention?
        WHAT_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_VE_ALREADY                                       = 10442,  -- What? Don't tell me you've already forgotten the recipe for astral matter. Oh well, not everyone can be as organized as yours truly! Anyway...
        WHY_YES_YES_I_D_RECOGNIZE_IT_ANYWHERE                                   = 10443,  -- Why, yes! Yes, I'd recognize it anywhere! One hundred percent pure, unadulterated astral whatchama-thingama-doodad-jiggity-callit!!! Now just sit tight for a moment, okay?
        YES_THIS_IS_IT_THE_GIZMO_THAT_WILL                                      = 10444,  -- Yes, this is it! The gizmo that will have synergists all over Vana'diel saying, Boy, how did I ever live without that nifty thingamadoo-diggity?
        I_DUB_IT_THE_PORTAFURNACE_AND_AS_A                                      = 10445,  -- I dub it the portafurnace! And as a reward for making this day possible, I present you with one of your very own!
        YOU_RE_IMPRESSED_AREN_T_YOU_GO_ON                                       = 10446,  -- You're impressed, aren't you? Go on and admit it! With this %, you can summon a synergy furnace to your side anytime, anywhere!
        ANYWHERE_THAT_IS_EXCEPT_FOR_BUSY_CITIES_AND                             = 10447,  -- Anywhere, that is, except for busy cities and towns. And dungeons. And inside buildings? And maybe some other places too. Mind you, that's not a defect--it's a feature! Safety first, I always say.
        NO_NO_YOU_DON_T_HAVE_TO_TELL                                            = 10448,  -- No, no, you don't have to tell me--I know I'm brilliant! Good day, and may my ingenious invention serve you well!
        WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_MY_FAVORITE_ADVENTURER                                 = 10449,  -- Well, if it isn't my favorite adventurer! Synergizing up a storm with the help of my miraculous portafurnace?
        YOU_LL_BE_HAPPY_TO_KNOW_THAT_I                                          = 10450,  -- You'll be happy to know that I'm already hard at work on my next invention: a doodad that can take that stuff from one of those whatsits, and convert it to pure whatchamacallit to use with the thingamajigs! Sounds amazing, doesn't it?
        WHAT_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_LOST_THE                                         = 10451,  -- What? Don't tell me you lost the % I made for you. I'm heartbroken! A lot of blood, sweat, and whatchamacallits go into making each and every one of those beauties!
        BUT_HEY_I_VE_GOT_A_SOFT_SPOT                                            = 10452,  -- But hey, I've got a soft spot for discombobulated types like you. Here's a brand-spankin' new one. Just promise me you'll hold onto it this time, okay?
        I_CAN_MAKE_YOU_ANOTHER_BUT_IT_LL                                        = 10453,  -- I can make you another, but it'll be a while before the doojigs are ready to toss into the thingamacallit. Why don't you come back a little later?
        YOU_RECEIVE_NOTHING_FROM_THE_MOON_RABBIT                                = 10455,  -- You receive nothing from the moon rabbit...
        THE_MOON_RABBIT_HAS_BROUGHT_ALONG_A_MONSTER                             = 10456,  -- The moon rabbit has brought along a monster!
        YOU_HAVE_TO_DO_SOMETHING_ABOUT_THOSE_CRAZY                              = 10457,  -- You have to do something about those crazy trees, kupo!
        YOU_RE_DONE_FIGHTING_TREES_KUPO                                         = 10458,  -- You're done fighting trees, kupo?
        HEY_YOU_I_LL_HAVE_YOU_KNOW_THAT                                         = 10466,  -- Hey, you! I'll have you know that only the rightful leader of the Star Onion Brigade can sit there! Get down right now before I charge you with trees-on and disturbing the peas!
        I_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_YOU_GOT_INSIDE                                         = 10467,  -- I don't know how you got inside, but that area is off limits. Vacate the premises immediately!
        HE_HE_HERE_S_YOUR_DELIVERY_WHEEZE                                       = 10468,  -- He...he...here's your delivery...<wheeze>...!
        THANKS_ONCE_AGAIN_LIGHT_ON_YOUR_FEET_TODAY                              = 10469,  -- Thanks once again. Light on your feet today, I see!
        WALKING_TREES_HOW_POSITIVELY_PECULIAR_ARE_THESE_ALSO                    = 10470,  -- Walking trees!? How positively...peculiar. Are these also creations conjured up with Tarutaru magic?
        WELCOME                                                                 = 10471,  -- Welcome!
        WHAT_CAN_I_DO_FOR_YOU                                                   = 10472,  -- What can I do for you?
        GO_BOTHER_SOMEONE_ELSE_I_M_BUSY                                         = 10473,  -- Go bother someone else. I'm busy!
        NEED_SOMETHING_SENT_TO_A_FRIEND_S_HOUSE                                 = 10474,  -- Need something sent to a friend's house? Sending items to your own house? You've come to the right place!
        EVTPARA_I_P_I_VJO_BV_BV_I                                               = 10475,  -- evtpara%I%p I[vjO ~bV ~bV %I%p ~bV s QS000 QS001 QS001AX QS001BX QS001BY QS001C pSDEF GR[z[NDEF
        IN_THE_GUSTABERG_MOUNTAINS_OF_SOUTHERN_QUON_LIES                        = 10476,  -- In the Gustaberg Mountains of Southern Quon lies the industrial nation known as the Republic of Bastok.
        COMPARED_TO_SAN_D_ORIA_WITH_ITS_LEGENDARY                               = 10477,  -- Compared to San d'Oria, with its legendary orders of knights, or Windurst, with its ancient institutes of magic, Bastok is still but a newborn nation.
        BUT_ADVANCED_TECHNOLOGY_AND_NEAR_LIMITLESS_UNDERGROUND_RESOURCES        = 10478,  -- But advanced technology and near limitless underground resources have allowed Bastok to rival the other two nations in power.
        INNOVATIVE_AND_ADAPTABLE_HUMES_MAKE_UP_MORE_THAN                        = 10479,  -- Innovative and adaptable Humes make up more than half the population of Bastok.
        WITH_THEIR_FLAIR_FOR_INDUSTRY_ECONOMY_AND_POLITICS                      = 10480,  -- With their flair for industry, economy, and politics, they were the driving force behind Bastok's rapid growth. Even now, Humes hold key positions in those areas.
        THE_GALKA_A_RACE_OF_HULKING_HUMANOIDS_COMPRISE                          = 10481,  -- The Galka, a race of hulking humanoids, comprise a third of Bastok's population. Originally hailing from Zepwell, they came to this land over six hundred years ago.
        WITHOUT_THEIR_INCOMPARABLE_STRENGTH_THE_COUNTLESS_ORE_MINES             = 10482,  -- Without their incomparable strength, the countless ore mines that drive Bastok's economy would never have been dug.
        ADVENTURERS_SEEKING_FAME_AND_FORTUNE_FLOCK_TO_RISING                    = 10483,  -- Adventurers seeking fame and fortune flock to rising nations like Bastok. You are one of them.
        YOUR_STORY_BEGINS_HERE_AMID_THE_SMOKE_AND                               = 10484,  -- Your story begins here, amid the smoke and bustle of the industrial city of Bastok.
        EXCUSE_ME                                                               = 10485,  -- Excuse me...
        HOW_DO_I_GET_TO_THE_RESIDENTIAL_AREA                                    = 10486,  -- How do I get to the residential area?
        ID_10487                                                                = 10487,  -- ...
        UH_HELLO_I_M_NEW_IN_BASTOK_CAN                                          = 10488,  -- Uh, hello. I'm new in Bastok. Can you tell me where the residential area is?
        OH_I_M_SORRY_I_DIDN_T_REALIZE                                           = 10489,  -- Oh! I'm sorry, I didn't realize you were new here, too.
        I_GUESS_I_LL_HAVE_TO_FIND_MY                                            = 10490,  -- I guess I'll have to find my way there myself. People aren't too friendly around here, are they?
        ANYWAYS_GOOD_LUCK_TO_THE_BOTH_OF_US                                     = 10491,  -- Anyways, good luck to the both of us!
        PESKY_HUME_WHERE_DOES_HE_THINK_HE_IS                                    = 10492,  -- Pesky Hume... Where does he think he is, Windurst? Some day this is turning out to be.
        YOU_RE_NOT_FROM_AROUND_HERE_EITHER_HUH                                  = 10493,  -- You're not from around here either, huh? No use denying it... I can smell it.
        IF_YOU_DON_T_WANT_TO_GET_HURT                                           = 10494,  -- If you don't want to get hurt, turn around and go back where you came from.
        HEY_HEY_THERE_S_NO_NEED_TO_BE                                           = 10495,  -- Hey, hey! There's no need to be rude.
        BESIDES_PICKING_ON_THIS_POOR_GUY_GIRL_ISN                               = 10496,  -- Besides, picking on this poor guy/girl] isn't worth it.
        OH_SINCE_WHEN_DO_YOU_CARE_WHAT_HAPPENS                                  = 10497,  -- Oh? Since when do you care what happens to outsiders, Gumbah?
        I_M_JUST_SAYING_THAT_ONE_SUCH_AS                                        = 10498,  -- I'm just saying that one such as you shouldn't bother with their like, O Great Warrior Deidogg.
        HRMPH_WHATEVER                                                          = 10499,  -- Hrmph. Whatever.
        YOU_JUST_REMEMBER_OUTSIDER_I_WON_T_GO                                   = 10500,  -- You just remember, outsider, I won't go so easy on you next time.
        SORRY_ABOUT_THAT_PEOPLE_CAN_BE_SO_HARD                                  = 10501,  -- Sorry about that. People can be so hard-headed around here sometimes.
        HEY_WHY_THE_GLUM_LOOK_DON_T_LIKE                                        = 10502,  -- Hey, why the glum look? Don't like being talked to like some new recruit? But it is your first time here, isn't it?
        FIRST_TIME_IN_BASTOK_YES_NO                                             = 10503,  -- First time in Bastok? Yes. No.
        REALLY_WELL_YOU_STILL_LOOK_LIKE_YOU_HAVEN                               = 10504,  -- Really? Well, you still look like you haven't been around much.
        IS_THERE_ANYTHING_YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_ANYTHING                             = 10505,  -- Is there anything you want to know? Anything you want to do? Maybe I can point you in the right direction.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_FIGHT_MONSTERS                                   = 10506,  -- What do you want to do? Fight monsters! Go shopping. Find some work.
        THEN_YOU_SHOULDN_T_HAVE_TO_COME_INTO                                    = 10507,  -- Then you shouldn't have to come into the city in the first place.
        GO_BACK_THE_WAY_YOU_CAME_AND_PASS                                       = 10508,  -- Go back the way you came and pass through the South Gate. That'll take you outside.
        OH_AND_MAKE_SURE_TO_ALWAYS_CHECK_MONSTERS                               = 10509,  -- Oh, and make sure to always check monsters out before fighting them. You don't want to pick fights with things you can't beat.
        THERE_ARE_SOME_SMALL_SHOPS_THROUGH_THAT_ARCH                            = 10510,  -- There are some small shops through that arch over there, but...
        IF_YOU_WANT_BETTER_STUFF_YOU_SHOULD_GO                                  = 10511,  -- If you want better stuff, you should go to the Markets.
        GOOD_CALL_YOU_SHOULD_START_WITH_A_SHORT                                 = 10512,  -- Good call. You should start with a short-term goal to get yourself on track. What kind of work are you looking for?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_SERVE_BASTOK                                     = 10513,  -- What do you want to do? Serve Bastok. Help people. Get rich, quick.
        YOU_SHOULD_GO_TALK_TO_A_GATE_GUARD                                      = 10514,  -- You should go talk to a gate guard. Try one of the town gates, like the one you just came through.
        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_COULD_YOU_DO_ME                                       = 10515,  -- That's the spirit! Could you do me a favor then, and help a friend of mine?
        IT_S_THE_FIRST_HOUSE_DOWN_THE_ROAD                                      = 10516,  -- It's the first house down the road through that big arch.
        WELL_IF_I_KNEW_ANYTHING_ABOUT_THAT_I                                    = 10517,  -- Well, if I knew anything about that, I wouldn't be here, would I?
        ANYWAY_MAYBE_ECHO_HAWK_CAN_HELP_YOU_HE                                  = 10518,  -- Anyway, maybe Echo Hawk can help you. He's got ears all over the place.
        TAKE_A_RIGHT_AND_GO_STRAIGHT_THROUGH_THAT                               = 10519,  -- Take a right and go straight through that entrance. He's usually lurking around there.
        OH_AND_TAKE_THIS_IT_S_ARVA_SHOULD                                       = 10520,  -- Oh, and take this. It's %. Arva should give you money for it. She's standing around the rear of the general goods store.
        DON_T_WORRY_IT_S_NOT_MINE_I                                             = 10521,  -- Don't worry, it's not mine. I just found it. Arva should be somewhere around...
        HERE_YOU_CAN_CHECK_YOUR_MAP_AGAIN_BY                                    = 10522,  -- Here. You can check your map again by selecting Map from the main menu on the right.
        OH_I_M_SURE_YOU_KNOW_THIS_ALREADY                                       = 10523,  -- Oh, I'm sure you know this already, but if you want to give items to people in town, use Trade from the main menu.
        I_GUESS_THAT_S_IT_I_HAVE_TO                                             = 10524,  -- I guess that's it. I have to run now, but I'm sure we'll meet again!
        I_HAVE_NOTHING_FOR_YOU_TODAY_SOMETIMES_EVEN                             = 10525,  -- I have nothing for you today. Sometimes, even I run out of information.
        WHAT_S_THIS_HAVEN_T_SEEN_YOU_AROUND                                     = 10526,  -- What's this? Haven't seen you around here before.
        FOR_A_NEWCOMER_YOU_RE_OFF_TO_A                                          = 10527,  -- For a newcomer, you're off to a good start... You've come to talk to me.
        I_M_ECHO_HAWK_I_TRADE_IN_INFORMATION                                    = 10528,  -- I'm Echo Hawk. I trade in information.
        DON_T_BOTHER_ASKING_THE_HARD_HEADED_GALKA                               = 10529,  -- Don't bother asking the hard-headed Galka around here--they're too busy contemplating their navels. But not me. I've got info on stuff most people have never even heard of.
        DON_T_WORRY_ABOUT_MONEY_I_MAKE_IT                                       = 10530,  -- Don't worry about money. I make it my policy not to take gil from rookies like you.
        MY_SOURCES_EVEN_PAY_ME_IN_SPECIAL_CASES                                 = 10531,  -- My sources even pay me in special cases, you know.
        ANYWAY_I_VE_HEARD_THAT_THIS_OLD_HUME                                    = 10532,  -- Anyway, I've heard that this old Hume, Wahid, is looking for a rare gem. You can find him at the auction house on the other side of this neighborhood.
        APPARENTLY_IT_S_SUPPOSED_TO_BE_PART_OF                                  = 10533,  -- Apparently, it's supposed to be part of some legend, but I don't deal with that kind of nonsense. Go talk to the bard at the tavern. Fairy tales are his specialty.
        YOU_CAN_PROBABLY_FIND_HIM_IN_THE_PORT                                   = 10534,  -- You can probably find him in the Port District. He's not the type to hang around this kind of seedy neighborhood.
        GOOD_HUNTING_THEN_COME_BACK_WHENEVER_YOU_NEED                           = 10535,  -- Good hunting, then. Come back whenever you need more info.
        YOU_ARE_AT_THE_SOUTH_GATE_IN_THE                                        = 10536,  -- You are at the South Gate, in the Bastok Mines District. The West Gate is in the Markets, while the North Gate in the port.
        EVER_SINCE_THE_NEW_PRESIDENT_CAME_INTO_OFFICE                           = 10537,  -- Ever since the new president came into office, all manner of public works are falling behind schedule.
        HE_SHOULDN_T_MEDDLE_WITH_THINGS_THAT_DON                                = 10538,  -- He shouldn't meddle with things that don't concern him, and let Chief Cid do his job. Doesn't he realize he's just a figurehead anyway?
        WHAT_THE_STAMP_HUNT_YOU_CAME_ALL_THIS                                   = 10539,  -- What? The stamp hunt? You came all this way for that, huh? Here you go.
        YOU_RECEIVED_A_STAMP                                                    = 10540,  -- You received a stamp!
        THERE_ARE_TWO_DUNGEONS_OUTSIDE_THE_CITY_OF                              = 10541,  -- There are two dungeons outside the city of Bastok: The Palborough Mines in North Gustaberg, and the Dangruf Wadi in South Gustaberg.
        THIS_NEIGHBORHOOD_S_PRETTY_ROUGH_BE_CAREFUL                             = 10542,  -- This neighborhood's pretty rough. Be careful.
        HMM_YOU_THE_NEW_MINER_NAH_YOU_LOOK                                      = 10543,  -- Hmm? You the new miner? Nah, you look like an adventurer. Here to pound some monsters into pudding, are you?
        JUST_DON_T_CAUSE_ANY_TROUBLE_ALL_RIGHT                                  = 10544,  -- Just don't cause any trouble, all right? We've got enough to worry about with these Galka. Only thing their long lives have given them are hard heads. Eesh.
        BASTOK_S_FOUNDATIONS_WERE_BUILT_WITH_THE_ORE                            = 10545,  -- Bastok's foundations were built with the ore taken from this mine. It took the Galka a lot of sweat and toil to dig this mine. We made Bastok what it is today.
        YEAH_USED_TO_HAVE_SOME_OF_THAT_A                                        = 10546,  -- %? Yeah, used to have some of that, a long time ago. Don't have any anymore, though.
        YOU_SHOULD_BE_ABLE_TO_FIND_SOME_NEAR                                    = 10547,  -- You should be able to find some near the coast of the Valkurm Dunes...but only during dust storms.
        THOSE_HUMES_ARE_FULL_OF_TALK_ABOUT_HOW                                  = 10548,  -- Those Humes are full of talk about how they dug the mythril mines with their great technology, but it didn't do them much good when the Quadav came, did it?
        WELCOME_TO_THE_PALBOROUGH_MINES_MADE_BY_HUMES                           = 10549,  -- Welcome to the Palborough Mines--made by Humes, full of Quadav. Good catch phrase for their mythril mines, don't you think?
        BASTOK_SURE_HAS_CHANGED_OVER_THE_YEARS_ABOUT                            = 10550,  -- Bastok sure has changed over the years. About the only things that don't change are us Galka, working in the mines.
        THERE_S_AN_INN_AND_THE_ALCHEMISTS_GUILD                                 = 10551,  -- There's an inn and the Alchemists' Guild through here, but other than that, you'll only find the homes of Bastok's poor. I don't think there's anything you'd want in there.
        WHAT_S_THE_MATTER_ARE_YOU_LOST                                          = 10552,  -- What's the matter? Are you lost?
        ASK_FOR_DIRECTIONS_ASK_DON_T_ASK                                        = 10553,  -- Ask for directions? Ask. Don't ask.
        WHERE_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_GO                                                 = 10554,  -- Where do you want to go?
        WHICH_AREA_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_ASK_ABOUT                                  = 10555,  -- Which area would you like to ask about? The South Gate and the residential area. The Markets and the Mines. The mining town and Alchemists' Guild. Uh, never mind.
        HMM_WELL_JUST_DON_T_WANDER_INTO_PLACES                                  = 10556,  -- Hmm. Well, just don't wander into places you don't know. It could be dangerous.
        SEE_THAT_BIG_BUILDING_SOUTH_FROM_HERE_ON                                = 10557,  -- See that big building south from here, on the left?
        THAT_S_THE_AUCTION_HOUSE_YOU_CAN_BUY                                    = 10558,  -- That's the auction house. You can buy other people's items or sell items yourself there.
        YOU_CAN_SEND_ITEMS_TO_YOUR_FRIENDS_THERE                                = 10559,  -- You can send items to your friends there as well. Just talk to the Galkan deliveryman on post.
        IF_YOU_KEEP_GOING_SOUTH_YOU_LL_FIND                                     = 10560,  -- If you keep going south, you'll find the South Gate.
        GO_THROUGH_IT_TO_GO_TO_SOUTH_GUSTABERG                                  = 10561,  -- Go through it to go to South Gustaberg. If you are a Bastoker, you can also receive missions from the guard at the gatehouse.
        IF_YOU_GO_LEFT_FROM_THE_SOUTH_GATE                                      = 10562,  -- If you go left from the South Gate toward the east, you'll come across another building.
        THAT_S_WHERE_YOU_LL_FIND_THE_CHOCOBO                                    = 10563,  -- That's where you'll find the Chocobo Stables. You can rent chocobos there to help you on those long trips.
        IF_YOU_GO_FURTHER_EAST_YOU_LL_COME                                      = 10564,  -- If you go further east, you'll come to the entrance to the residential area. Go on inside if you want to drop off items in your room.
        IF_YOU_ARE_NOT_FROM_BASTOK_HOWEVER_YOU                                  = 10565,  -- If you are not from Bastok, however, you'll need to get a Rent-a-Room first.
        GO_THROUGH_THE_ARCH_WEST_OF_HERE                                        = 10566,  -- Go through the arch west of here.
        YOU_WILL_SEE_A_ROAD_SLOPING_DOWN_ON                                     = 10567,  -- You will see a road sloping down on your right. Walk down that road to go to the Markets district.
        IF_YOU_GO_STRAIGHT_WEST_YOU_LL_BE                                       = 10568,  -- If you go straight west, you'll be able to see the entrance to the mines.
        INSIDE_THE_MINES_YOU_WILL_FIND_MINERS_OF                                = 10569,  -- Inside the mines you will find miners, of course--but also monsters. You should be careful.
        TO_THE_NORTH_OF_THIS_FORK_THERE_ARE                                     = 10570,  -- To the north of this fork there are two arches, one big and one small.
        THE_BIG_ARCH_LEADS_TO_THE_LOWER_LEVEL                                   = 10571,  -- The big arch leads to the lower level of the mining town, while the small one leads to its surface level.
        IF_YOU_WALK_THROUGH_THE_SMALL_ARCH_TO                                   = 10572,  -- If you walk through the small arch to the surface level, you'll find an inn to your left.
        ACROSS_FROM_THE_INN_IS_THE_ARMORY                                       = 10573,  -- Across from the inn is the armory.
        IF_YOU_GO_FURTHER_DOWN_THE_ROAD_YOU                                     = 10574,  -- If you go further down the road, you'll come across a goods shop and the back exit of the mining town.
        GO_THROUGH_THE_EXIT_AND_YOU_LL_BE                                       = 10575,  -- Go through the exit and you'll be behind the auction house.
        YOU_LL_ALSO_FIND_STAIRS_OFF_TO_THE                                      = 10576,  -- You'll also find stairs off to the side, midway down the mining town street. Those connect the surface and lower levels.
        AT_THE_FAR_END_OF_THE_LOWER_LEVEL                                       = 10577,  -- At the far end of the lower level, to the east, is where you'll find the Alchemists' Guild.
        THAT_S_ABOUT_IT_I_CAN_EXPLAIN_IT                                        = 10578,  -- That's about it. I can explain it to you again, but it might be better for you to just go to those places yourself and talk to the people there.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_THIS_IS_NO_PLACE                                       = 10579,  -- What do you want? This is no place for the likes of you. Get out.
        WHAT_GUMBAH_SENT_YOU_YOU_SAY                                            = 10580,  -- What? Gumbah sent you, you say?
        THAT_HE_WOULD_ASK_A_NEWBORN_PUP_LIKE                                    = 10581,  -- That he would ask a newborn pup like you... Are his eyes failing him, at such a young age?
        WELL_I_SUPPOSE_YOU_LL_JUST_HAVE_TO                                      = 10582,  -- Well, I suppose you'll just have to do. He put his trust in you, so I must do the same.
        I_AM_CURRENTLY_EMPLOYED_BY_THE_TENSHODO_AND                             = 10583,  -- I am currently employed by the Tenshodo, and my task is to collect five % for them.
        ALAS_I_WAS_INJURED_WHEN_I_OBTAINED_THE                                  = 10584,  -- Alas, I was injured when I obtained the fourth. It will be some time before I can go out to find the fifth.
        THE_TENSHODO_TOOK_THE_FIRST_FOUR_BUT_THEY                               = 10585,  -- The Tenshodo took the first four, but they refuse to hand me my reward until the last one is in their hands.
        I_AM_SURE_THEY_WOULD_NOT_HAVE_TOLD                                      = 10586,  -- I am sure they would not have told me that had I not been injured.
        IF_YOU_WOULD_COULD_YOU_GIVE_TALIB_OF                                    = 10587,  -- If you would, could you give Talib of the Tenshodo the last %, in my name?
