        BUT_I_HAVEN_T_THE_FOGGIEST_IDEA_OF_2                                    = 11001,  -- But...I haven't the foggiest idea of how to get either of these things, kupo... Whatever am I to do, kupo?
        MASTER_I_M_OVERWHELMED_BY_YOUR_KINDNESS_KUPO_2                          = 11002,  -- Master! I'm overwhelmed by your kindness, kupo!!!
        I_LL_BRING_YOU_A_NICE_PRESENT_FROM_2                                    = 11003,  -- I'll bring you a nice present from the moogles' hometown, kupo! I'll be back in a few days, kupo!
        MASTER_I_M_BACK_FROM_MY_VACATION_KUPO_2                                 = 11004,  -- Master! I'm back from my vacation, kupo!
        HERE_S_YOUR_PRESENT_THE_BEHEMOTH_OF_MOG                                 = 11005,  -- Here's your present--the behemoth of Mog Safes, kupo! Now you can store as many as 70 items, kupo!
        THE_CAPACITY_OF_YOUR_MOG_SAFE_HAS_INCREASED                             = 11006,  -- The capacity of your Mog Safe has increased!
        MASTER_MASTER_I_HAVE_A_FAVOR_TO_ASK_3                                   = 11007,  -- Master, Master! I have a favor to ask, kupo!
        AFTER_RESTING_ON_THE_I_NOTICED_A_LETTER                                 = 11008,  -- After resting on the %, I noticed a letter had arrived from some old moogle friends, kupo! Will my magnanimous master give me some time off to go visit my old buddies?
        GIVE_YOUR_MOOGLE_SOME_TIME_OFF_HAVE_FUN                                 = 11009,  -- Give your moogle some time off? Have fun, kupo! No, I am your only friend now!
        OH_THANK_YOU_MASTER_MY_MOOGLE_FRIENDS_LIVE                              = 11010,  -- Oh, thank you, master! My moogle friends live across the seas, so I have another favor to ask you, kupo!
        THE_SUN_BEATS_DOWN_MERCILESSLY_IN_THE_LAND                              = 11011,  -- The sun beats down mercilessly in the land beyond the west sea, so I need to take % for my friends there, kupo!
        AND_MY_OTHER_BUDDIES_NEED_FOR_THE_TORRENTIAL                            = 11012,  -- And my other buddies need % for the torrential rains that scour the lands across the east sea, kupo!
        I_CAN_T_HELP_OUT_MY_FRIENDS_IF                                          = 11013,  -- I can't help out my friends if I don't have % and %, kupo...
        I_LL_BE_SURE_TO_BRING_YOU_A                                             = 11014,  -- I'll be sure to bring you a souvenir from my overseas trip, kupo! See you in a few days, master!
        MASTER_I_M_BACK_FROM_VISITING_MY_OLD                                    = 11015,  -- Master! I'm back from visiting my old moogle friends, kupo!
        WE_ALL_GOT_TOGETHER_AND_MADE_YOU_A                                      = 11016,  -- We all got together and made you a new Mog Safe, kupo! Now you can store as many as 80 items, kupo!
        I_AM_VIRNAGE_A_FRIAR_FROM_THE_SAN                                       = 11017,  -- I am Virnage, a friar, from the San d'Oria Cathedral. Coming to Bastok is part of my pilgrimage.
        I_WAS_TO_RETURN_TO_SAN_D_ORIA                                           = 11018,  -- I was to return to San d'Oria after praying at the Crag of Dem...
        BUT_I_VE_SEEN_SOMETHING_HORRIBLE_HERE_THAT                              = 11019,  -- But I've seen something horrible here that demanded that I stay. The statue of the Goddess in the Metalworks--yes, its placement is deplorable, too--its paint is peeling off!
        I_CANNOT_BELIEVE_THAT_NO_ONE_HERE_NOTICED                               = 11020,  -- I cannot believe that no one here noticed! That statue's paint is specifically made to endure the rigors of time! It is supposed to last dozens of years!
        AH_BUT_THERE_IS_HOPE_I_ONCE_READ                                        = 11021,  -- Ah, but there is hope. I once read an account of friars carrying off a batch of paint with them as they sought a place of safety during the Great War!
        THEY_STAYED_IN_A_CITADEL_ON_THE_SAUROMUGUE                              = 11022,  -- They stayed in a citadel on the Sauromugue Champaign. The paint may be there still! I have heard people here say you are a great adventurer. Please, help the Goddess in Her hour of need!
        PLEASE_THE_GODDESS_NEEDS_YOUR_HELP                                      = 11023,  -- Please, the Goddess needs your help!
        AH_YOU_VE_FOUND_THE_MAY_THE_GODDESS                                     = 11024,  -- Ah! You've found the %! May the Goddess bless your soul!
        I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_REPAY_YOU_FOR_YOUR                                      = 11025,  -- I would like to repay you for your deeds, but I have nothing to give you at the moment.
        HERE_I_WILL_GIVE_YOU_THIS_LETTER_BRING                                  = 11026,  -- Here, I will give you this letter. Bring it to Eperdur in the San d'Oria Cathedral. I am sure he will give you a reward.
        MAY_THE_GATES_OF_PARADISE_OPEN_FOR_YOU                                  = 11027,  -- May the Gates of Paradise open for you.
        HAND_MY_LETTER_TO_EPERDUR_IN_THE_SAN                                    = 11028,  -- Hand my letter to Eperdur in the San d'Oria Cathedral to claim your reward.
        THE_GODDESS_S_IMAGE_HAS_BEEN_RESTORED_YET                               = 11029,  -- The Goddess's image has been restored! Yet...I've received word from the cathedral that my pilgrimage is not yet complete.
        THE_GATES_OF_PARADISE_ARE_VERY_FAR_INDEED                               = 11030,  -- The Gates of Paradise are very far, indeed...
        GOOD_DAY_YOUNG_WHIPPER_SNAPPER_YOU_LOOK_AS                              = 11031,  -- Good day, young whipper-snapper. You look as if you've been working hard.
        GOOD_DAY_YOUNG_LAD_LASS_I_CAN_SEE                                       = 11032,  -- Good day, young lad/lass]. I can see that you've become quite the adventurer. When you get to be my age, you can tell these things, you know.
        MY_DARLING_SON_MAY_HIS_SOUL_REST_IN                                     = 11033,  -- My darling son, may his soul rest in peace, was a warrior, and so was my grandson...until he decided to quit and become a doorman.
        MY_SON_DIDN_T_TEACH_HIM_HOW_TO                                          = 11034,  -- My son didn't teach him how to wield a sword so he could go waste his skill on being a doorman. That boy just doesn't understand...
        HE_DIDN_T_EVEN_TAKE_HIS_FATHER_S                                        = 11035,  -- He didn't even take his father's sword with him.
        SURE_IT_MAY_BE_A_LITTLE_OLD_AND                                         = 11036,  -- Sure, it may be a little old and may need a few repairs. I think that the handle requires some kind of special part...
        I_REMEMBER_MY_SON_SAYING_HE_HAD_FOUND                                   = 11037,  -- I remember my son saying he had found % in a tent when he and some great Galka named Ragarimin, or something like that, went on an expedition to the Orcs' stronghold.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_STOP_BY_THERE_ON                                       = 11038,  -- If you happen to stop by there on your way somewhere, picking some up would make me ever so grateful.
        WELL_I_LL_BE_YOU_VE_BROUGHT_ME                                          = 11039,  -- Well I'll be! You've brought me %! I'll ask my sweetie in the Blacksmiths' Guild to fix it all up, good as new.
        I_M_SORRY_I_HAVE_NO_WAY_TO                                              = 11040,  -- I'm sorry. I have no way to repay you now. Could you please come back tomorrow?
        THANKS_TO_YOU_MY_SON_S_SWORD_IS                                         = 11041,  -- Thanks to you, my son's sword is as good as it was the day it was forged. I'm sorry to bother you any further, but could you take this to my grandson?
        TO_GET_TO_WHERE_HE_S_STATIONED_I                                        = 11042,  -- To get to where he's stationed, I hear you have to ride this newfangled elevatie contraption.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_DOORMEN_GET_DECENT_PAY_SO                                 = 11043,  -- They say that doormen get decent pay, so you can get your reward from my grandson. I'm sure he won't mind.
        HIS_NAME_OH_IT_S_NAJI                                                   = 11044,  -- His name? Oh, it's Naji.
        SO_YOU_TOOK_THE_SWORD_TO_MY_GRANDSON                                    = 11045,  -- So, you took the sword to my grandson? Hmm...and the sword was connected to that Sir Ragimorimm character?
        NOW_THAT_YOU_MENTION_IT_WHEN_SIR_RAGAMUFFIMM                            = 11046,  -- Now that you mention it, when Sir Ragamuffimm was a young'un, he was always acting all grown-up. Why do you suppose that is..?
        ALL_THOSE_GALKA_PRAISING_THE_LIKES_OF_HIM                               = 11047,  -- All those Galka praising the likes of him... Except for one. There was one who hated that Sir Ragamamm.
        YES_I_REMEMBER_MY_SON_HAVING_A_BIT                                      = 11048,  -- Yes, I remember my son having a bit of trouble with that fellow. I think his name was Deidogolly, or something like that.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_LOOKING_AT                                     = 11049,  -- What do you think you're looking at? Huh? Deidogolly? What did that old Phara woman say? That nonsense has nothing to do with me.
        WHAT_YOU_RE_STILL_HERE_I_DON_T                                          = 11050,  -- What? You're still here? I don't know anything about any pesky old Hume woman. Raogrimm and Yasin? Yeah, I knew them. Raogrimm and I were the same age, too.
        SURE_HE_WAS_THE_TALEKEEPER_SURE_WHEN_HE                                 = 11051,  -- Sure, he was the Talekeeper. Sure, when he was reborn the same year as I was, he had two hundred years of knowledge.
        OF_COURSE_I_HATED_HIM_RAOGRIMM_THE_KNOW                                 = 11052,  -- Of course I hated him. Raogrimm the know-it-all, acting like an elder when he was just a kid... Always adored by everyone...
        AND_ON_TOP_OF_THAT_BECOMING_A_MUSKETEER                                 = 11053,  -- And on top of that, becoming a Musketeer to win the favor of the Humes--how low can you get!? I even heard rumors that he was having relations with one of their females.
        YEAH_YEAH_I_HEARD_THE_STORY_ABOUT_HIM                                   = 11054,  -- Yeah, yeah. I heard the story about him taking down some mighty Quadav in the Palborough Mines, but I don't believe it.
        HE_WAS_TOLD_TO_BRING_BACK_A_CERTAIN                                     = 11055,  -- He was told to bring back a certain item as proof, but you know, he never did.
        THE_BEAST_DID_NOT_CARRY_ONE_THAT_S                                      = 11056,  -- The beast did not carry one. That's what he said, but it's a lie. A lie he told to gain fame. I bet you he never went anywhere near the beast's lair.
        YOU_SEEM_STRONG_ENOUGH_WHY_DON_T_YOU                                    = 11057,  -- You seem strong enough. Why don't you go and see if you can take down that Quadav? They say it appears deep in the Palborough Mines in some room where the Quadav keep their eggs.
        IF_YOU_CAN_BRING_BACK_THEN_IT_WILL                                      = 11058,  -- If you can bring back %, then it will prove that Raogrimm was a fake!
        WHAT_YOU_MANAGED_TO_GET_THIS_PROVES_IT                                  = 11059,  -- What!? You managed to get %!? This proves it! Raogrimm was a liar!
        TALEKEEPER_HAH_HE_WAS_NOTHING_BUT_A_FAKE                                = 11060,  -- Talekeeper... Hah! He was nothing but a fake!
        GREETINGS_DEIDOGG                                                       = 11061,  -- Greetings, Deidogg.
        YOU_IF_IT_ISN_T_PAGDAKO_I_MEAN                                          = 11062,  -- You! If it isn't Pagdako...I mean, Iron Eater. What, the Humes finally let you off your leash?
        I_HAVE_SOME_BUSINESS_IN_THIS_AREA_BUT                                   = 11063,  -- I have some business in this area, but that is of no importance. I hear that you have been speaking ill of Sir Raogrimm again.
        YEAH_YEAH_I_HAVE_AND_WHY_NOT_RAOGRIMM                                   = 11064,  -- Yeah...yeah, I have. And why not? Raogrimm lied about killing that Quadav just to gain fame.
        WHAT_ARE_YOU_IMPLYING                                                   = 11065,  -- ...What are you implying?
        AH_I_SEE_YOU_ARE_STILL_GOING_ON                                         = 11066,  -- Ah, I see. You are still going on about that...
        SIR_RAOGRIMM_FOUGHT_THE_BEASTMEN_FOR_THE_GOOD                           = 11067,  -- Sir Raogrimm fought the beastmen for the good of his countrymen. He would never steal trophies for his own profit or fame.
        THE_ORDER_WAS_FOR_HIM_TO_TAKE_DOWN                                      = 11068,  -- The order was for him to take down the Quadav, not to retrieve the item.
        AND_I_HAVE_ALSO_HEARD_THAT_SIR_RAOGRIMM                                 = 11069,  -- And, I have also heard that Sir Raogrimm himself questioned many of his orders, finding them at odds with his moral beliefs.
        WHAT_DOES_THAT_HAVE_TO_DO_WITH_ANYTHING                                 = 11070,  -- What does that have to do with anything!?
        BUT_THERE_WAS_ONE_TIME_AND_ONE_TIME                                     = 11071,  -- But there was one time, and one time only, when Sir Raogrimm took an item from a monster.
        HE_NEEDED_IT_TO_FINISH_A_NEW_PAIR                                       = 11072,  -- He needed it to finish a new pair of greaves he had promised to a friend.
        GREAVES_YOU_DON_T_MEAN                                                  = 11073,  -- Greaves... You don't mean...
        HE_TRAVELED_TO_CASTLE_OZTROJA_TO_OBTAIN_A                               = 11074,  -- He traveled to Castle Oztroja to obtain a rare % from the leeches there... It was with this item that he completed his friend's greaves.
        THAT_FRIEND_WOULD_ALWAYS_TALK_ILL_OF_HIM                                = 11075,  -- That friend would always talk ill of him, but was the only one who would treat him as an equal.
        I_CAN_T_WHY_WOULD_HE_THERE_IS                                           = 11076,  -- I can't... Why would he... There is no way he could go all the way to Oztroja...a-and I've never heard of such an item anyway.
        WHERE_DID_YOU_GET_THIS                                                  = 11077,  -- %! Where did you get this!?
        SO_YOU_REALLY_DO_GET_THESE_FROM_THE                                     = 11078,  -- So you really do get these from the leeches in Castle Oztroja... He went all the way there to keep his promise...
        YES_I_DO_HAVE_GREAVES_MADE_OF_THIS                                      = 11079,  -- Yes, I do have greaves made of this material. They were sent to me with an unsigned note that only said, The greaves I promised.
        HIS_PROMISE_IT_HAD_TO_BE_WHEN                                           = 11080,  -- His promise... It had to be when...
        RAOGRIMM_WHAT_S_KEEPING_YOU                                             = 11081,  -- Raogrimm! What's keeping you?
        MY_APOLOGIES_THE_CEREMONIAL_OUTFITS_ADULTS_GIVE_ME                      = 11082,  -- My apologies. The ceremonial outfits adults give me are too cumbersome--especially these shoes.
        WHATEVER_IT_SOUNDS_TO_ME_LIKE_YOU_RE                                    = 11083,  -- Whatever. It sounds to me like you're just spoiled. You're the Talekeeper, right? You should be able to choose your own shoes.
        BUT_I_CAN_T_JUST_IGNORE_THEIR_GOOD                                      = 11084,  -- But I can't just ignore their good will.
        OH_COME_ON_HERE_YOU_CAN_HAVE_THESE                                      = 11085,  -- Oh, come on! Here, you can have these. They're pretty light. Don't worry, I got two pairs the other day.
        THANKS_HOW_CAN_I_REPAY_YOU                                              = 11086,  -- Thanks... How can I repay you?
        YOU_THE_BOY_WHO_CAN_GET_ANYTHING_HE                                     = 11087,  -- You, the boy who can get anything he wants? I don't need any of that junk. When you get strong enough to go out on your own, you can get me something a hundred times better than the shoes I just gave you.
        IT_MUST_HAVE_BEEN_THAT_PROMISE_WHY_WOULD                                = 11088,  -- It must have been that promise... Why would he remember something stupid like that? Even I didn't remember until now...
        ANYWAY_I_THANK_YOU_THOSE_GREAVES_ARE_OLD                                = 11089,  -- Anyway, I thank you. Those greaves are old now, but I can repair them with this new %.
        MY_DAYS_OF_BATTLE_ARE_OVER_I_WOULD                                      = 11090,  -- My days of battle are over. I would like you to have the greaves. Stop by tomorrow morning to pick them up.
        I_VE_FINISHED_THE_GREAVES_THESE_HOLD_THE                                = 11091,  -- I've finished the greaves. These hold the soul of Raogrimm. Use them as he would have.
        I_HATE_SAYING_THIS_TO_AN_OUTSIDER_LIKE                                  = 11092,  -- I hate saying this to an outsider like you, but...thanks. And that's all I'm going to say.
        HEY_REMEMBER_WHEN_IRON_EATER_SHOWED_UP_HERE                             = 11093,  -- Hey, remember when Iron Eater showed up here?
        HE_WAS_GATHERING_INFORMATION_ABOUT_RAOGRIMM_I_HEAR                      = 11094,  -- He was gathering information about Raogrimm. I hear that they are starting up some operation to collect his lost items...
        AND_SO_I_GOT_THIS_IDEA                                                  = 11095,  -- And so I got this idea...
        WAIT_I_CAN_T_BE_ASKING_OUTSIDERS_FOR                                    = 11096,  -- ...Wait. I can't be asking outsiders for help. It's just not like me. Forget what I said!
        OH_IF_IT_ISN_T_GWILL_SO_WHAT                                            = 11097,  -- Oh, if it isn't Gwill. So what's the occasion? Is Dalzakk off adventuring?
        YEAH                                                                    = 11098,  -- Yeah...
        YOU_DON_T_LOOK_SO_GOOD_GWILL_YOU                                        = 11099,  -- You don't look so good, Gwill. You're not being teased by those Hume kids again, are you?
        WELL_NOT_REALLY_TEASED                                                  = 11100,  -- Well, not really teased...
        YOU_WIMP_WHY_DO_YOU_LET_THOSE_CREEPS                                    = 11101,  -- You wimp! Why do you let those creeps push you around like that? With your strength, you could teach them a lesson.
        IF_YOU_WON_T_DO_IT_I_COULD                                              = 11102,  -- If you won't do it, I could always...
        NO_NO_THAT_S_OKAY_IT_S_JUST                                             = 11103,  -- No, no. That's okay... It's just that Arawn and Emrys don't understand...
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_DON_T_UNDERSTAND                                       = 11104,  -- What do you mean, don't understand?
        DETZO_DO_YOU_THINK_THAT_TASTE_GOOD                                      = 11105,  -- Detzo, do you think that % taste good?
        HUH_WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_WELL_I_VE                                          = 11106,  -- Huh? What do you mean? Well, I've never tried one anyway, so I wouldn't know. But from what I hear, they're supposed to taste pretty good.
        I_GUESS_I_D_HAVE_TO_TRY_ONE                                             = 11107,  -- I guess I'd have to try one to really find out.
        YEAH_WELL_THE_THING_IS_I_HAVE_TRIED                                     = 11108,  -- Yeah... Well, the thing is, I have tried one before. Dalzakk brought some back from his adventures once. Anyway, it was really good.
        WHEN_I_TOLD_THIS_TO_ARAWN_AND_EMRYS                                     = 11109,  -- When I told this to Arawn and Emrys, they said that there was no way that a cookie with ginger in it could be that delicious.
        THAT_S_SO_STUPID_THEY_RE_STUPID_FOR                                     = 11110,  -- That's so stupid... They're stupid for saying something like that, and you are just as stupid for getting all upset over it.
        IF_YOU_CAN_T_STICK_UP_FOR_YOURSELF                                      = 11111,  -- If you can't stick up for yourself over something like that, then you shouldn't talk to those guys anymore. Just stay home and read books like you always do, you pitiful excuse for a Galka!
        OKAY_BYE                                                                = 11112,  -- Okay... Bye...
        WHAT_A_CASE_YOU_KNOW_I_THINK_I                                          = 11113,  -- What a case! You know, I think I heard somebody talking about %...
        YEAH_I_REMEMBER_NOW_DEIDOGG_SAID_THAT_HE                                = 11114,  -- Yeah, I remember now. Deidogg said that he used to eat them with his friend a long time ago.
        HEY_ISN_T_THIS_WHERE_DID_YOU_GET                                        = 11115,  -- Hey. Isn't this %? Where did you get this?
        I_SEE_DETZO_HAS_A_BIG_MOUTH_YEAH                                        = 11116,  -- ...I see Detzo has a big mouth. Yeah, this brings back memories. Raogrimm and I always used to eat these.
        THAT_S_RIGHT_YOU_RE_THE_ONE_WHO                                         = 11117,  -- That's right. You're the one who wanted to hear about the operation to find some of Raogrimm's lost items.
        MANY_YEARS_AGO_RAOGRIMM_WAS_SENT_AS_AN                                  = 11118,  -- Many years ago, Raogrimm was sent as an envoy to San d'Oria. As a gesture of friendship, he offered his armor to the Knights of San d'Oria.
        BUT_APPARENTLY_IT_WAS_RECENTLY_STOLEN_TO_SAN                            = 11119,  -- But apparently it was recently stolen. To San d'Oria, this is an enormous blunder, and the high-ups in Bastok are determined to get it back first.
        BASTOK_WANTS_TO_USE_THE_ARMOR_AS_A                                      = 11120,  -- Bastok wants to use the armor as a bargaining tool with San d'Oria. Unbelievable what outrageous plans those Humes think up...
        HEY_WHY_DON_T_YOU_TRY_TO_FIND                                           = 11121,  -- Hey, why don't you try to find it before the Musketeers do? I'd rather an adventurer like you have that armor than seeing it turned into a political tool for those idiots in the government.
        I_HEARD_THAT_THE_ONES_WHO_STOLE_RAOGRIMM                                = 11122,  -- I heard that the ones who stole Raogrimm's armor are a group of Goblin thieves that keep their hideout in the Behemoth's Dominion.
        VANA_DIEL_IS_ABUZZ_WITH_ADVENTURER_APPRECIATION_FEVER                   = 11123,  -- Vana'diel is abuzz with Adventurer Appreciation fever, kupo!
        WE_MOOGLES_HAVE_PREPARED_SOME_NICE_LITTLE_GOODIES                       = 11124,  -- We moogles have prepared some nice little goodies and gathered lots of top-secret information on adventurer activity, kupo! Let me check my journal for your statistical data...
        CHAT_FREQUENCY_CONVERSATIONS_WITH_NPCS_PARTIES_JOINED_ALLIANCES         = 11125,  -- Chat Frequency: # Conversations With NPCs: # Parties Joined: # Alliances Joined: #
        BATTLES_FOUGHT_NUMBER_OF_TIMES_KO_D_ENEMIES                             = 11126,  -- Battles Fought: # Number of Times KO'd: # Enemies Defeated: # GM Calls Made: #
        THERE_S_YOUR_ADVENTURING_LIFE_IN_A_NUTSHELL                             = 11127,  -- There's your adventuring life in a nutshell!
        THERE_S_YOUR_ADVENTURING_LIFE_IN_A_NUTSHELL_2                           = 11128,  -- There's your adventuring life in a nutshell! And this time, there's an extra-special anniversary present involved! Oh, just be careful you don't accidentally throw it away or anything, because you'll never be able to get another one...ever, kupo!
        TAKE_A_LOOK_AND_TO_THINK_YOU_CAN                                        = 11129,  -- Take a look--and to think, you can select # more amazing anniversary items!
        TAKE_A_LOOK_AND_TO_THINK_YOU_CAN_2                                      = 11130,  -- Take a look--and to think, you can select # more amazing anniversary item!
        WHICH_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_REMAINING_I_NEED_TIME                              = 11131,  -- Which would you like? (# remaining) I need time to think. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %.
        AH_I_UNDERSTAND_WITH_SOME_MANY_GOODIES_TO                               = 11132,  -- Ah, I understand. With some many goodies to choose from, it's no surprise that you'd want to think about it a bit more. I'll be here once you've decided, kupo.
        REMAINING_YES_NO                                                        = 11133,  -- %? (# remaining) Yes. No.
        AN_EXCELLENT_CHOICE_I_HOPE_YOU_ENJOY_YOUR                               = 11134,  -- An excellent choice! I hope you enjoy your brand-new %!
        THERE_S_YOUR_ADVENTURING_LIFE_IN_A_NUTSHELL_3                           = 11135,  -- There's your adventuring life in a nutshell! And because it seems you're so eager to get your hands on some more goodies, I guess I could find it in my heart to spare another...but just for you, kupo!
        YOU_HAVE_THE_CHOICE_TO_EITHER_RECEIVE_YOUR                              = 11136,  -- You have the choice to either receive your present now, or wait to build up the suspense, kupo!
        IF_YOU_CHOOSE_TO_WAIT_YOU_MIGHT_FIND                                    = 11137,  -- If you choose to wait, you might find yourself receiving an even better present, kupo.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_KUPO_LEMME_THINK_KUPO                                  = 11138,  -- What will you do, kupo? Lemme think, kupo. Gimme my present, kupo! I'll wait, kupo.
        TAKE_ALL_THE_TIME_YOU_NEED_AND_TALK                                     = 11139,  -- Take all the time you need, and talk to me when you're ready, kupo!
        HERE_S_YOUR_PRESENT_KUPO                                                = 11140,  -- Here's your present, kupo!
        KUPOPOPO_A_PATIENT_ONE_LET_S_SEE_HOW                                    = 11141,  -- Kupopopo! A patient one! Let's see how long you can wait before the suspense finally gets to you, kupo!
        GOOD_LUCK_I_WILL_BESTOW_UPON_YOU_YOUR                                   = 11142,  -- Good luck, [citizen/comrade]. I will bestow upon you your nation's Signet.
        I_CANNOT_HELP_YOU_YOU_SHOULD_GO_FIND                                    = 11143,  -- I cannot help you. You should go find a guard from your own country.
        I_CANNOT_ACCEPT_CRYSTALS_FROM_SOMEONE_WHOSE_RANK                        = 11144,  -- I cannot accept crystals from someone whose rank is still 1. I advise you to either keep them until your reach rank 2, or to use them in craftwork.
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_SAN_D_ORIA                                     = 11145,  -- Since we are allied with San d'Oria...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_BASTOK                                         = 11146,  -- Since we are allied with Bastok...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_WINDURST                                       = 11147,  -- Since we are allied with Windurst...
        I_AM_SORRY_I_AM_TOO_BUSY_WITH                                           = 11148,  -- I am sorry. I am too busy with other matters to be speaking with you.
        AH_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_SUPPLIES_THESE_WILL                              = 11149,  -- Ah, you have brought us supplies. These will help us indeed. I thank you.
        HMM_THESE_SUPPLIES_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_ARE                              = 11150,  -- Hmm... These supplies you have brought us are too old to be of any use. We will dispose of them promptly. I do commend you for your effort. May you succeed next time.
        YOU_VE_EARNED_CONQUEST_POINTS                                           = 11151,  -- You've earned conquest points!
        YOU_VE_RECEIVED_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                = 11152,  -- You've received your nation's Signet. You are now taking part in your nation's conquest campaign!
        I_AM_A_TEMPLE_KNIGHT_I_AM_ONE                                           = 11153,  -- I am , a Temple Knight. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing San d'Oria's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_AN_IRON_MUSKETEER_I_AM_ONE                                         = 11154,  -- I am , an Iron Musketeer. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Bastok's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_A_WAR_WARLOCK_I_AM_ONE                                             = 11155,  -- I am , a War Warlock. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Windurst's conquest campaign.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_BUSINESS_WOULD_YOU_CAST_SIGNET                             = 11156,  -- What is your business? Would you cast Signet on me? I want to spend my conquest points. [I want to join the Expeditionary Force./Teleport me to the E.F. area.] I want to quit the E.F./change my E.F. I want to go on a supplies quest. I have some questions... Nothing, sorry to bother you.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_NOTHING                                  = 11157,  -- What do you wish to know about? Nothing. Conquests. Conquest results. Donating crystals. Conquest points. The effects of controlling regions. Regions controlled by other nations. Regions under beastman control.
        ALL_THREE_NATIONS_ARE_STRIVING_DAILY_TO_PUT                             = 11158,  -- All three nations are striving daily to put more regions under their control. This is what we call conquests. You can take part in it and serve your country by defeating enemies while you have Signet cast on you.
        EACH_REGION_COMPRISES_SEVERAL_AREAS_AND_THE_NATION                      = 11159,  -- Each region comprises several areas, and the nation that rids those areas of the most monsters gains control of the region.
        NATIONS_RECEIVE_GOODS_AND_RESOURCES_FROM_REGIONS_UNDER                  = 11160,  -- Nations receive goods and resources from regions under their control.
        SO_THE_MORE_REGIONS_WE_CONTROL_THE_RICHER                               = 11161,  -- So, the more regions we control, the richer our nation becomes.
        BORDER_GUARDS_ARE_ALSO_PLACED_IN_OUTPOSTS_WITHIN                        = 11162,  -- Border guards are also placed in outposts within regions under our control. They are there to cast Signet on adventurers like yourself.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                  = 11163,  -- Once you have your nation's Signet, you will be able to acquire crystals from enemies you defeat.
        NOT_ONLY_THAT_BUT_YOU_WILL_ALSO_RECEIVE                                 = 11164,  -- Not only that, but you will also receive conquest points. You get more conquest points if you defeat enemies in regions that are not under your nation's control. These points can be used to purchase items from guards like myself.
        SO_YOU_SEE_CONQUESTS_BENEFIT_NATIONS_AND_ADVENTURERS                    = 11165,  -- So you see...conquests benefit nations and adventurers alike. We expect you to do your best to serve your country.
        YOU_CAN_SEE_THE_CURRENT_STATE_OF_CONQUESTS                              = 11166,  -- You can see the current state of conquests by selecting Region Info from the main menu. Conquest results in all regions are regularly recalculated, so you may want to check them from time to time.
        SHOPS_IN_OUR_CITY_WILL_BE_SELLING_DIFFERENT                             = 11167,  -- Shops in our city will be selling different items according to our conquest rank. The Troupe Valeriano will also visit the nation that finishes first and bring a little joy to its citizens.
        YOU_CAN_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO_YOUR_NATION_ONCE                             = 11168,  -- You can donate crystals to your nation once you achieve rank 2. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        WE_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO                                 = 11169,  -- We would like you to donate crystals to your nation from now on. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        YOU_CAN_ACQUIRE_CRYSTALS_BY_DEFEATING_ENEMIES_WHILE                     = 11170,  -- You can acquire crystals by defeating enemies while you have your nation's Signet. Having Signet cast on you is also the only way of taking part in conquests.
        RANK_POINTS_WILL_BE_AWARDED_TO_YOU_FOR                                  = 11171,  -- Rank points will be awarded to you for each crystal you donate, and you may be offered new missions as your rank goes up.
        YOU_ALSO_RECEIVE_RANK_POINTS_FOR_COMPLETING_MISSIONS                    = 11172,  -- You also receive rank points for completing missions. Complete missions and take part in conquests to raise your rank and serve your country.
        YOU_ARE_AWARDED_CONQUEST_POINTS_WHEN_YOU_DEFEAT                         = 11173,  -- You are awarded conquest points when you defeat monsters while you are taking part in conquests. Select "Region Info" from the menu to check your current number of conquest points.
        YOU_CAN_PURCHASE_ITEMS_FROM_GUARDS_LIKE_MYSELF                          = 11174,  -- You can purchase items from guards like myself with your conquest points, but be warned that the number of points you spend will be subtracted from your current total.
        WHEN_CONQUEST_RESULTS_ARE_ANNOUNCED_YOU_WILL_BE                         = 11175,  -- When conquest results are announced, you will be told which country controls the region you are in at that time. Sometimes regions may become neutral, or beastmen may even gain control of regions.
        IF_WE_GAIN_CONTROL_OF_A_REGION_BORDER                                   = 11176,  -- If we gain control of a region, border guards will be placed at its outposts to help adventurers like you.
        MERCHANTS_WILL_ALSO_BE_PLACED_THERE_AND_GOODS                           = 11177,  -- Merchants will also be placed there, and goods from that region will find their way to the local shops here.
        GAINING_CONTROL_OF_REGIONS_IS_THE_BASIC_PRINCIPLE                       = 11178,  -- Gaining control of regions is the basic principle behind conquests. We need each of you to do your best, and bring our nation to the top of the ranks.
        OF_COURSE_SOMETIMES_WE_LOSE_REGIONS_TO_OTHER                            = 11179,  -- Of course, sometimes we lose regions to other nations...so we must try to take them back before the next conquest results are announced.
        AS_AN_INCENTIVE_WE_WILL_AWARD_YOU_WITH                                  = 11180,  -- As an incentive, we will award you with more conquest points for defeating monsters in those regions.
        BUT_IF_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_ANOTHER_NATION                                = 11181,  -- But if we are allied with another nation, you will only be awarded the regular rate for defeating monsters in our allies' regions. On the other hand, we will award you with more points for fighting in the top-ranked nation's regions.
        OUR_PARAMOUNT_CONCERN_LIES_IN_THE_BEASTMEN_GAINING                      = 11182,  -- Our paramount concern lies in the beastmen gaining control of our regions. If too many of us are defeated in a region, the beastmen will gain control of it.
        IF_THIS_HAPPENS_NOT_ONLY_IS_IT_A                                        = 11183,  -- If this happens, not only is it a great blow to our pride, but you will be unable to acquire any crystals in that region.
        THE_BEASTMEN_ARE_A_MENACE_TO_ALL_NATIONS                                = 11184,  -- The beastmen are a menace to all nations. If they rise to power, we must all unite and drive those vile creatures from that region.
        WE_NEED_YOU_TO_BRING_SUPPLIES_TO_THE                                    = 11185,  -- We need you to bring supplies to the outpost border guards who are placed in regions under our control.
        THERE_IS_ONE_OUTPOST_IN_EACH_REGION_SELECT                              = 11186,  -- There is one outpost in each region. Select Region Info from the menu, and look for the areas with a small flag mark on the map. That is where they are.
        HERE_ARE_THE_SUPPLIES_JUST_GIVE_THEM_TO                                 = 11187,  -- Here are the supplies. Just give them to the guard at the outpost and your mission will be complete. Now, choose which outpost you want to go to. We give different rewards for each region, so choose carefully.
        WHERE_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_TAKE_THE_SUPPLIES                                  = 11188,  -- Where do you wish to take the supplies? @ @ @ @ @ The Ronfaure Region.[/ (Done)] The Zulkheim Region.[/ (Done)] The Norvallen Region.[/ (Done)] The Gustaberg Region.[/ (Done)] The Derfland Region.[/ (Done)] The Sarutabaruta Region.[/ (Done)] The Kolshushu Region.[/ (Done)] The Aragoneu Region.[/ (Done)] The Fauregandi Region.[/ (Done)] The Valdeaunia Region.[/ (Done)] Qufim Island.[/ (Done)] The Li'Telor Region.[/ (Done)] The Kuzotz Region.[/ (Done)] The Vollbow Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Lowlands Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Uplands Region.[/ (Done)] Tu'Lia.[/ (Done)] @ The Tavnazian Archipelago.[/ (Done)] @ @ @ @ @ @ @ Cancel.
        WHICH_E_F_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_JOIN                                        = 11189,  -- Which E.F. would you like to join? . . . . . . The Zulkheim Region (Lv.20`). The Norvallen Region (Lv.25`). . The Derfland Region (Lv.25`). . The Kolshushu Region (Lv.20`). The Aragoneu Region (Lv.25`). The Fauregandi Region (Lv.35`). The Valdeaunia Region (Lv.40`). The Qufim Region (Lv.25`). The Li'Telor Region (Lv.35`). The Kuzotz Region (Lv.40`). The Vollbow Region (Lv.65`). The Elshimo Lowlands Region (Lv.35`). The Elshimo Uplands Region (Lv.45`). . . . . . . . . . . None.
        SO_BE_IT_YOU_HAVE_UNTIL_THE_NEXT                                        = 11190,  -- So be it. You have until the next conquest results announcement to complete this mission. Good luck.
        WE_WILL_DISPOSE_OF_THOSE_UNUSABLE_SUPPLIES                              = 11191,  -- We will dispose of those unusable supplies.
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_UNDERTAKE_ONE_SUPPLY_MISSION_PER                           = 11192,  -- You can only undertake one supply mission per day. Come back later.
        I_AM_SORRY_WE_SEEM_TO_HAVE_A                                            = 11193,  -- I am sorry. We seem to have a problem. Let me cancel it.
        YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_DONATE_ANY_MORE                                      = 11194,  -- You do not need to donate any more crystals at your current rank. Speak to the guard at the gatehouse for further instructions.
        YOUR_RANK_POINTS_ARE_FULL_WE_VE_ADDED                                   = 11195,  -- Your rank points are full. We've added the excess to your conquest points. You do not need to donate any more crystals. Go to the gatehouse for further instructions.
