        THE_SIDE_THAT_SUCCEEDS_IN_LIGHTING_ALL_OF                               = 12074,  -- The side that succeeds in lighting all of its Flammen-Brenner will be declared the winner after a specified amount of time.
        IF_NEITHER_SIDE_IS_VICTORIOUS_BEFORE_THE_MATCH                          = 12075,  -- If neither side is victorious before the match ends, the outcome will be judged based on the score. The match score section of the rulebook contains more information on this subject.
        BRENNER_IS_SIGNIFICANTLY_DIVIDED_INTO_PUBLIC_AND_PRIVATE                = 12076,  -- Brenner is significantly divided into public and private matches. Official matches are held periodically according to level and feature general participation.
        YOU_CANNOT_RESERVE_THE_ISLE_WHEN_AN_OFFICIAL                            = 12077,  -- You cannot reserve the Isle when an official match is being held.
        NO_ITEMS_ARE_NECESSARY_FOR_PARTICIPATION_BUT_A                          = 12078,  -- No items are necessary for participation, but a minor fee will be collected. You will be unable to participate if your level is too low.
        THE_MATCH_OUTCOME_WILL_BE_RECORDED_UNLESS_THE                           = 12079,  -- The match outcome will be recorded unless the number of participants fails to exceed # members, or if there are fewer than # members in a match where the two sides' numbers differ. In such cases, the game will be considered a training match and will not be recorded.
        PRIVATE_MATCHES_REQUIRE_A_RESERVATION_AND_PARTICIPATION_MAY             = 12080,  -- Private matches require a reservation, and participation may be limited. The Master of Ceremonies (MC) can freely adjust the rules and control match proceedings.
        LS_LIGA_IS_A_FORM_OF_PRIVATE_MATCH                                      = 12081,  -- LS Liga is a form of private match. You can learn more about LS Liga by speaking to a Marshal.
        A_FLAMMEN_BRENNER_IS_A_DEVICE_THAT_CONTAINS                             = 12082,  -- A Flammen-Brenner is a device that contains a Flamme (flame). The Flammen-Brenner is covered by a grate that will open after taking a set amount of damage, exposing the Flamme.
        THE_PARTICIPANTS_MUST_UTILIZE_THIS_CHANCE_TO_SEIZE                      = 12083,  -- The participants must utilize this chance to seize the Flamme before the grate recloses. Once the grate is closed, the Flammen-Brenner will begin recovering from the damage it has been dealt.
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_OPEN_THE_OPPOSING_TEAM                                 = 12084,  -- If you manage to open the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner and capture their Flamme, you should make haste to light one of the Flammen-Brenner on your side.
        AFTER_A_CERTAIN_AMOUNT_OF_TIME_THE_FLAMME                               = 12085,  -- After a certain amount of time, the Flamme will burn out and the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner will be relit.
        ALSO_PLEASE_NOTE_THAT_YOU_CANNOT_QUICKEN_YOUR                           = 12086,  -- Also, please note that you cannot quicken your pace using any special abilities while you are in possession of a Flamme.
        IN_THE_EVENT_THAT_NEITHER_SIDE_FULFILLS_THE                             = 12087,  -- In the event that neither side fulfills the conditions for victory, the outcome of the match will be evaluated based on score.
        TEN_POINTS_ARE_AWARDED_TO_EACH_SIDE_FOR                                 = 12088,  -- Ten points are awarded to each side for every lit Flammen-Brenner, while one point is awarded whenever a Flamme is captured, used to light a Flammen-Brenner, or recaptured from an opponent. One point is also awarded for protecting the Flammen-Brenner for a certain period of time.
        LIKE_BALLISTA_QUARRY_QUARRY_CAN_BE_USED_WHILE                           = 12089,  -- Like Ballista, quarry (/quarry) can be used while playing Brenner. Participants may use this ability to dig up Petras and temporary items.
        HOWEVER_UNLIKE_BALLISTA_PETRAS_BRENNER_PETRAS_HAVE_NO                   = 12090,  -- However, unlike Ballista Petras, Brenner Petras have no effect on the match score. You can trade a Petra to a Pursuivant to recover your HP and MP at no expense to TP.
        SPRINT_CANNOT_BE_USED_WHILE_CARRYING_A_PETRA                            = 12091,  -- Sprint cannot be used while carrying a Petra. Also, please note that the scout ability cannot be used in Brenner.
        PETRAS_WILL_BE_LOST_IN_THE_EVENT_OF                                     = 12092,  -- Petras will be lost in the event of a KO, but can be carried over from one match to another.
        THE_SPRINT_SPRINT_ABILITY_CAN_BE_USED_TO                                = 12093,  -- The sprint (/sprint) ability can be used to increase the player's speed when not in possession of a Flamme or Petras.
        IN_THE_EVENT_OF_A_KO_YOU_WILL                                           = 12094,  -- In the event of a KO, you will be returned to your team's camp. However, recovery will take longer the more often you fall in battle.
        IN_OTHER_WORDS_YOU_WILL_RECEIVE_A_PENALTY                               = 12095,  -- In other words, you will receive a penalty if you fall immediately after recovering from KO. In addition, your TP will be reduced to zero and you will lose any Petras in your possession.
        I_M_SORRY_I_WASN_T_LISTENING_COULD                                      = 12096,  -- I'm sorry. I wasn't listening. Could you start over from the beginning?
        WHAT_S_THIS_YOU_SAY_YOU_FOUND_MY                                        = 12097,  -- What's this? You say you found my old name tag?
        PUFF_HUFF_JUST_A_MOMENT_ADVENTURER                                      = 12098,  -- <Puff...huff...> Just a...moment...adventurer...
        WHAT_S_THE_MEANING_OF_DESERTIFYING_ME_LIKE                              = 12099,  -- What's the meaning of desertifying me like that?
        IF_WE_DON_T_SHOW_THE_TAG_TO                                             = 12100,  -- If we don't show the tag to Pavuluke, we can't make progress in our investimigation!
        MISTER_PAVALAKE_PLEASE_TAKE_A_LOOK_AT_THIS                              = 12101,  -- Mister Pavalake! Please take a look at this!
        MY_NAME_IS_PAVVKE_BUT_MORE_IMPORTANTLY_WHERE                            = 12102,  -- My name is Pavvke... But more importantly, where did you find this?
        YES_YES_PAVVKE_THAT_S_WHAT_I_SAID                                       = 12103,  -- Yes, yes, Pavvke, that's what I said. This tag was discoverified in the Moblin settlement that recently appeared in North Gustaberg.
        THE_NOMADIC_TOWN_OF_MOVALPOLOS_BACK_AGAIN_HUH                           = 12104,  -- The nomadic town of Movalpolos... Back again, huh?
        MO_VAL_PO_LOS                                                           = 12105,  -- Mo...val...po...los?
        YES_THE_MOBLINS_CARRY_THIS_CITY_WITH_THEM                               = 12106,  -- Yes, the Moblins carry this city with them as they tunnel through the earth.
        ALMOST_A_HUNDRED_YEARS_AGO_OUR_EXPANSION_OF                             = 12107,  -- Almost a hundred years ago, our expansion of the Gusgen Mines ran into the tunnels being dug by the Moblins.
        WHAT_WHY_WAS_I_NEVER_INFORMARIZED_ABOUT_THIS                            = 12108,  -- What!? Why was I never informarized about this!?
        AT_THE_TIME_BASTOK_WAS_INVOLVED_WITH_THE                                = 12109,  -- At the time, Bastok was involved with the elimination of Mithran pirates terrorizing the southern seas.
        HUME_OFFICIALS_PROBABLY_KNOW_NEXT_TO_NOTHING_ABOUT                      = 12110,  -- Hume officials probably know next to nothing about our battle with Movalpolos.
        YOU_MUST_BE_SPEAKING_OF_THE_ELSHIMO_CAMPAIGN                            = 12111,  -- You must be speaking of the Elshimo Campaign. Windurst was falsely accuserized by the governments of Bastok and Tavnazia...
        DID_YOU_JUST_MENTIONIFY_A_BATTLE_WITH_THE                               = 12112,  -- ...Did you just mentionify a battle with the inhabitants of Movalpolos?
        ARE_YOU_TELLING_US_THAT_THE_MOBLINS_STARTED                             = 12113,  -- Are you telling us that the Moblins started warification on you?
        HMM_THE_MOBLINS_RETREATED_INTO_THEIR_CITY_AND                           = 12114,  -- Hmm. The Moblins retreated into their city and only emerged to kidnap people and steal books.
        HOWEVER_THEY_WEREN_T_ATTACKING_US_AS_SUCH                               = 12115,  -- However, they weren't attacking us as such. Even the people who were kidnapped were returned unharmed.
        THEN_ONE_GALKA_DECIDED_HE_WOULD_LEARN_THE                               = 12116,  -- Then one Galka decided he would learn the Moblin language and try to reason with them.
        BUT_HIS_ATTEMPTS_ENDED_IN_FAILURE_THE_MOBLINS                           = 12117,  -- But his attempts ended in failure... The Moblins suddenly became hostile and dangerous.
        WHAT_A_CALAMITY_WHAT_KIND_OF_WORDS_WERE                                 = 12118,  -- What a calamity! What kind of words were exchangified, I wonder!?
        I_SUPPOSIFY_GALKA_AREN_T_KNOWN_FOR_THEIR                                = 12119,  -- I supposify Galka aren't known for their diplomacy...
        NOBODY_REALLY_KNOWS_WHAT_PASSED_BETWEEN_THEM_IN                         = 12120,  -- Nobody really knows what passed between them. In any case, the battle ended as abruptly as it had begun.
        ONE_MORNING_WE_AWOKE_TO_DISCOVER_THAT_THE                               = 12121,  -- One morning, we awoke to discover that the tunnel connecting the mines to Movalpolos had completely caved in. The Moblins had left.
        SO_THEY_FLED_THINKING_THEY_WOULD_BE_OBLITERAFICATED                     = 12122,  -- So they fled, thinking they would be obliteraficated?
        I_DON_T_THINK_SO_BASTOK_HAD_NO                                          = 12123,  -- I don't think so. Bastok had no formal army. It had come to the point where we had even considered collapsing the Gusgen Mines.
        THEN_PERHAPS_THEY_HAD_ACHIEVERIZED_SOME_GOAL                            = 12124,  -- Then, perhaps they had achieverized some goal?
        I_DON_T_KNOW_THE_ONLY_PERSON_WHO                                        = 12125,  -- I don't know. The only person who knows what really happened back then would be Jabbos, the Galka who tried talking with the Moblins.
        AND_WHERE_CAN_THIS_GALKA_BE_LOCATIFIED                                  = 12126,  -- And where can this Galka be locatified?
        NOBODY_KNOWS_HE_DISAPPEARED_ON_THE_FIRST_DAY                            = 12127,  -- Nobody knows. He disappeared on the first day of our battle with Movalpolos.
        I_GUESS_HE_WAS_ASHAMED_AT_THE_TROUBLE                                   = 12128,  -- I guess he was ashamed at the trouble he had caused.
        HE_RAN_AWAY_THAT_DOESN_T_SEEM_VERY                                      = 12129,  -- He ran away? That doesn't seem very Galka-ized to me.
        ID_12130                                                                = 12130,  -- ...
        WELL_DON_T_DESPAIRIFY_MISTER_PAKUKE                                     = 12131,  -- Well, don't despairify, Mister Pakuke!
        RHINOSTERY_RESEARCHERS_FROM_THE_FEDERATION_OF_WINDURST_ARE              = 12132,  -- Rhinostery researchers from the Federation of Windurst are dispatchimicated to every corner of Vana'diel. We'll locatify him for you!
        THIS_IS_A_GREAT_DEVELOPMENT_NOW_WE_KNOW                                 = 12133,  -- This is a great development! Now we know that communification can take place with the Moblins if we manage to learn their language!
        I_MUST_REPORTIFICATE_TO_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_AYAME_AND                     = 12134,  -- I must reportificate to Mythril Musketeer Ayame and delay the deployerization of the troops.
        HERE_S_YOUR_REMUNERAFICATION_TAKE_CARE_BYE_BYE                          = 12135,  -- Here's your remunerafication. Take care, bye bye now!
        I_AM_VIRNAGE_A_FRIAR_FROM_THE_SAN_2                                     = 12136,  -- I am Virnage, a friar from the San d'Orian Cathedral. Coming to Bastok is part of my pilgrimage.
        I_WAS_PERMITTED_TO_PERUSE_THE_HOLY_TOME                                 = 12137,  -- I was permitted to peruse the holy tome that was found in the Moblin lair below North Gustaberg.
        IT_IS_WITHOUT_A_DOUBT_A_VOLUME_PRINTED                                  = 12138,  -- It is, without a doubt, a volume printed by the San d'Orian Cathedral. Judging by its relatively unsullied condition, the book appears to have been handled with care and reverence.
        IF_THESE_MOBLINS_TRULY_BELIEVE_IN_THE_GRACE                             = 12139,  -- If these Moblins truly believe in the grace of the Goddess Altana, I cannot abandon them to the ungentle ministrations of the Republic.
        HOWEVER_IT_WOULD_BE_FOOLISH_OF_ME_TO                                    = 12140,  -- However, it would be foolish of me to venture alone into a beastman lair without further confirmation of their faith.
        WOULD_YOU_BE_WILLING_TO_DISCOVER_THE_TRUTH                              = 12141,  -- Would you be willing to discover the truth behind this theological enigma?
        ARE_YOU_WILLING_TO_DISCOVER_THE_TRUTH_READY                             = 12142,  -- Are you willing to discover the truth? Ready and able. I can't handle the truth.
        MY_MOST_HUMBLE_THANKS_THIS_IS_A_TALISMAN                                = 12143,  -- My most humble thanks. ...This is a talisman bearing the symbol of the Goddess.
        THE_SAME_SYMBOL_ADORNS_THE_COVER_OF_THE                                 = 12144,  -- The same symbol adorns the cover of the holy tome. Presenting the talisman to the Moblins should help you determine where their true faith lies.
        THE_BEARS_THE_SAME_SYMBOL_THAT_ADORNS_THE                               = 12145,  -- The % bears the same symbol that adorns the book of worship. Presenting this to the Moblins should help you determine where their true faith lies.
        HOW_DID_YOU_FARE_WAS_THE_TALISMAN_WELL                                  = 12146,  -- How did you fare? Was the talisman well-received?
        GREAT_GODDESS_YOU_WERE_ATTACKED                                         = 12147,  -- Great Goddess! You were attacked!?
        WERE_MY_HOPES_IN_VAIN_THOUGH_THEY_DID                                   = 12148,  -- Were my hopes in vain? Though they did not ally themselves with the Shadow Lord, these Moblins do live in a world without the blessing of light.
        I_MUST_CONCLUDE_THAT_THE_CAREFUL_TREATMENT_OF                           = 12149,  -- I must conclude that the careful treatment of the holy tome had more to do with its value as a curiosity, rather than as an object of faith.
        HOWEVER_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_DAWN_GODDESS_IN                               = 12150,  -- However, the symbol of the Dawn Goddess in your possession assured you safe passage back to the surface world. Do you not agree?
        WHAT_SAY_YOU_I_WILL_MAKE_YOU_A                                          = 12151,  -- What say you? I will make you a gift of the talisman in return for a small donation to the cathedral...
        HM_YOU_SAY_THE_TALISMAN_WAS_TAKEN_BY                                    = 12152,  -- Hm? You say the talisman was taken by a Galka that spoke the Moblin tongue?
        AND_HE_DISAPPEARED_INTO_THE_DEPTHS_OF_MOVALPOLOS                        = 12153,  -- And he disappeared into the depths of Movalpolos after saving you from the enraged Moblins?
        HM_YOU_SAY_THE_TALISMAN_WAS_TAKEN_BY_2                                  = 12154,  -- Hm? You say the talisman was taken by a Moblin that spoke the common tongue?
        AND_HE_MENTIONED_A_GALKA_HAD_TAUGHT_HIM                                 = 12155,  -- And he mentioned a Galka had taught him how to speak our language?
        THIS_GALKA_MUST_BE_A_PERSON_OF_SOME                                     = 12156,  -- This Galka must be a person of some importance in the Moblin city.
        PERHAPS_HE_WAS_THE_ORIGINAL_OWNER_OF_THE                                = 12157,  -- Perhaps he was the original owner of the holy tome you retrieved.
        WE_MUST_REPORT_THE_EXISTENCE_OF_THIS_GALKA                              = 12158,  -- We must report the existence of this Galka to Ayame of the Mythril Musketeers.
        IF_THESE_BEASTMEN_ARE_CAPABLE_OF_LIVING_ALONGSIDE                       = 12159,  -- If these beastmen are capable of living alongside people, we cannot simply brand them as villains...
        PLEASE_ACCEPT_YOUR_REWARD_MAY_PARADISE_OPEN_ITS                         = 12160,  -- Please accept your reward. May Paradise open its gates to you.
        I_WAS_THINKING_THIS_OUT_LOUD_WHEN_AN                                    = 12161,  -- I was thinking this out loud when an Elvaan girl passing by stopped to talk to me.
        BUT_WHAT_ABOUT_MOOGLES_THEY_VE_GOT_WINGS                                = 12162,  -- But what about moogles? They've got wings, and they can fly, but you wouldn't call 'em birds. They've got those funny antennae, too, but they're not insects, either.
        WHEN_I_RESPONDED_TO_HER_REMARK_WITH_THE                                 = 12163,  -- When I responded to her remark with the fact that both moogles and chocobos are animals, this is what she asked:
        THEN_WHAT_S_THE_DIFFERENCE_BETWEEN_ANIMALS_AND                          = 12164,  -- Then what's the difference between animals and people?
        I_ANSWERED_PEOPLE_ARE_SMARTER_THAN_ANIMALS_AND                          = 12165,  -- I answered, People are smarter than animals. And then she retorted, People sure are more sly!
        AHAHAHA_DON_T_GET_ALL_HUFFY_ON_ME                                       = 12166,  -- Ahahaha, don't get all huffy on me! I stopped to talk because what you were saying was important.
        PEOPLE_ARE_ALL_DIFFERENT_FROM_ONE_ANOTHER_THEY                          = 12167,  -- People are all different from one another. They're different from animals, and different from plants. This difference is what makes it all worth it.
        THERE_ARE_LOTS_OF_WAYS_TO_THINK_AND                                     = 12168,  -- There are lots of ways to think and feel, and things to know and to believe. But in the end, we all come from the same source.
        THAT_S_TRUE_FOR_BOTH_PEOPLE_AND_ANIMALS                                 = 12169,  -- That's true for both people and animals.
        WE_ALL_HAVE_THIS_THING_CALLED_A_SOUL                                    = 12170,  -- We all have this thing called a soul. The souls of animals are pure and simple.
        LOOK_OVER_THERE_THAT_CHOCOBO_IS_LIVING_PROOF                            = 12171,  -- Look over there. That chocobo is living proof.
        YOU_SHOULD_ASK_SOMEONE_HOW_THAT_CHOCOBO_WAS                             = 12172,  -- You should ask someone how that chocobo was born. Then you'll have your answers.
        AND_THEN_SHE_WENT_ON_HER_WAY                                            = 12173,  -- ...And then she went on her way.
        I_WENT_TO_FIND_OUT_HOW_THAT_CHOCOBO                                     = 12174,  -- I went to find out how that chocobo was born, but no one could tell me.
        SHALOTT_SAID_THE_CHOCOBO_S_MOTHER_WAS_FROM                              = 12175,  -- Shalott said the chocobo's mother was from the stables in Bastok.
        SHE_SAID_IT_WAS_A_SPECIAL_CHOCOBO_THAT                                  = 12176,  -- She said it was a special chocobo that had silver-colored feathers on its neck.
        HOW_I_WISH_I_COULD_GO_TO_BASTOK                                         = 12177,  -- How I wish I could go to Bastok to see her for myself.
        I_WONDER_IF_THAT_ELVAAN_GIRL_WILL_BE                                    = 12178,  -- I wonder if that Elvaan girl will be passing by again anytime soon...
        THAT_ELVAAN_GIRL_TOLD_ME_THAT_BOTH_PEOPLE                               = 12179,  -- That Elvaan girl told me that both people and animals have souls. She said that the souls of animals are far more pure than those of people.
        SHE_ALSO_TOLD_ME_I_WOULD_UNDERSTAND_WHAT                                = 12180,  -- She also told me I would understand what she meant if I found out how that chocobo was born.
        ACCORDING_TO_SHALOTT_THE_CHOCOBO_S_MOTHER_IS                            = 12181,  -- According to Shalott, the chocobo's mother is from the stables in Bastok. How I wish I could go there to see her for myself...
        WHAT_CAN_I_DO_FOR_YOU_IF_YOU                                            = 12182,  -- What can I do for you? If you want to ride a chocobo, one of the girls over there can help you out.
        LATELY_A_LOT_OF_ADVENTURERS_SEEM_TO_BE                                  = 12183,  -- Lately, a lot of adventurers seem to be forgetting that a chocobo is an animal, not an object.
        YOU_SHOULD_KEEP_THAT_IN_MIND_AS_YOU                                     = 12184,  -- You should keep that in mind as you're enjoying that easy ride through monster-ridden badlands. Have a safe journey.
        A_CHOCOBO_WITH_SILVER_COLORED_FEATHERS                                  = 12185,  -- A chocobo with silver-colored feathers...?
        AH_YOU_D_BE_TALKING_ABOUT_SILVER_COMET                                  = 12186,  -- Ah, you'd be talking about Silver Comet.
        SHE_USED_TO_BE_THE_MOUNT_OF_A                                           = 12187,  -- She used to be the mount of a highly ranked general in the Bastokan navy.
        THE_GENERAL_S_SON_RECEIVED_THE_CHOCOBO_AS                               = 12188,  -- The general's son received the chocobo as a coming-of-age present, which he promptly took advantage of to leave Bastok.
        FOR_THE_LONGEST_TIME_NO_ONE_SAW_HIDE                                    = 12189,  -- For the longest time, no one saw hide nor hair of man or beast--until eventually, Silver Comet came wandering back into town...alone.
        I_HEARD_LATER_ON_THAT_THE_GENERAL_S                                     = 12190,  -- I heard later on that the general's son had lost his life somewhere in the wilds.
        ONLY_SILVER_COMET_HAD_MANAGED_TO_RETURN_UNHARMED                        = 12191,  -- Only Silver Comet had managed to return unharmed.
        IN_MEMORY_OF_HIS_SON_THE_GENERAL_ASKED                                  = 12192,  -- In memory of his son, the general asked us to take the chocobo into our care...
        BUT_THEN_ONE_DAY_SILVER_COMET_WAS_GONE                                  = 12193,  -- But then one day, Silver Comet was gone. Some chocobo thief had stolen her.
        HM_YOU_SAY_A_CHICK_OF_SILVER_COMET                                      = 12194,  -- Hm? You say a chick of Silver Comet's is being kept in the Jeuno stables? You must be mistaken.
        ANYWAY_AFTER_THE_THEFT_THE_GENERAL_EXHAUSTED_EVERY                      = 12195,  -- Anyway, after the theft, the general exhausted every avenue in search of his son's chocobo.
        HE_EVENTUALLY_FOUND_AN_ADVENTURER_WHO_ALLEGEDLY_SAW                     = 12196,  -- He eventually found an adventurer who allegedly saw a chocobo drowning in the Pashhow Marshlands.
        THAT_CHOCOBO_HAD_THE_SAME_MARKINGS_AS_SILVER                            = 12197,  -- That chocobo had the same markings as Silver Comet.
        IF_YOU_WANT_TO_TRY_TALKING_TO_THAT                                      = 12198,  -- If you want to try talking to that adventurer, you should go to the outpost in the marshlands.
        HE_S_GIVEN_UP_THE_ADVENTURING_LIFE_IT                                   = 12199,  -- He's given up the adventuring life, it seems. Now he earns his daily bread by seeing to the needs of the soldiers at the outpost.
        THE_GATE_IS_LOCKED                                                      = 12200,  -- The gate is locked.
        WHADDAYA_WANT_I_GOT_NO_TIME_FOR_ADVENTURERS                             = 12201,  -- Whaddaya want? I got no time for adventurers.
        HUH_WHERE_D_YOU_HEAR_WELL_WHATEVER                                      = 12202,  -- Huh? Where'd you hear... Well, whatever.
        YOU_SAY_YOU_GOT_BUSINESS_WITH_ME                                        = 12203,  -- You say you got business with me?
        SILVER_COMET_WHAT_THE_HELL_ARE_YOU_BOTHERING                            = 12204,  -- Silver Comet... What the hell are you bothering me about that old chocobo story for? You some kind of crackpot?
        LEAVE_ME_ALONE_YOU_LOON                                                 = 12205,  -- Leave me alone, you loon.
        CAN_T_YOU_SEE_I_M_BUSY_THIS                                             = 12206,  -- Can't you see I'm busy? This place gets too wet and too dark too quick to be wasting time chatting.
        HOLD_UP_A_MINUTE_IF_YOU_BRING_ME                                        = 12207,  -- Hold up a minute. If you bring me some %, I might be willing to give you the time of day.
        YEP_THREE_OF_THOSE_OUGHT_TO_DO_IT                                       = 12208,  -- Yep, three of those ought to do it. I'll give you until the day after tomorrow.
        YOU_BROUGHT_WHAT_I_ASKED_FOR_CAREFUL_WITH                               = 12209,  -- You brought what I asked for? Careful with that stuff, it's powerful smelly.
        IT_S_GOOD_FOR_HIDING_A_PERSON_S                                         = 12210,  -- It's good for hiding a person's scent, you see. Helps me get around.
        NOW_THEN_YOU_WANTED_TO_HEAR_ABOUT_THAT                                  = 12211,  -- Now, then. You wanted to hear about that chocobo, right?
        SHE_WAS_ONE_OF_THE_FASTEST_CHOCOBOS_I                                   = 12212,  -- She was one of the fastest chocobos I've ever ridden, but damn near uncontrollable. I don't know how Silver Comet's owner handled her.
        I_GUESS_THE_DEATH_OF_HER_FORMER_OWNER                                   = 12213,  -- I guess the death of her former owner is what sent her off the edge. That chocobo wasn't right in the head.
        SHE_THREW_HERSELF_HEADLONG_INTO_THE_MARSHES_THOUGHT                     = 12214,  -- She threw herself headlong into the marshes. Thought my number was up, I can tell you!
        WHEN_I_SAW_HER_IN_THE_STABLES_SHE                                       = 12215,  -- When I saw her in the stables, she was wearing a collar attached to a chain.
        THAT_WASN_T_TO_KEEP_THE_GENERAL_S                                       = 12216,  -- That wasn't to keep the general's mount from being stolen--it was to keep Silver Comet from flying the coop, so to speak.
        THAT_GENERAL_S_A_REAL_SCHEMER_SAID_THAT                                 = 12217,  -- That general's a real schemer. Said that if Silver Comet was released, she would be able to find Shooting Star.
        IT_S_HIS_FAULT_I_ALMOST_GOT_KILLED                                      = 12218,  -- It's his fault I almost got killed!
        HUH_WHO_S_SHOOTING_STAR_HE_S_A                                          = 12219,  -- Huh? Who's Shooting Star? He's a chocobo, too.
        SHOOTING_STAR_WAS_SILVER_COMET_S_MATE                                   = 12220,  -- Shooting Star was Silver Comet's mate.
        THEIR_LOVE_WAS_A_PURE_UNCOMPLICATED_THING_MUCH                          = 12221,  -- Their love was a pure, uncomplicated thing, much more so than what people feel.
        AHAHAHA_I_THINK_THIS_OIL_IS_STARTING_TO                                 = 12222,  -- Ahahaha! I think this oil is starting to muddle my senses. I'll see you around, adventurer.
        WERE_YOU_ABLE_TO_MEET_WITH_THAT_ADVENTURER                              = 12223,  -- Were you able to meet with that adventurer?
        IS_THAT_RIGHT_I_THINK_YOU_WERE_AROUND                                   = 12224,  -- ...Is that right? I think you were around that % a bit too long.
