        UGH_LEAVE_IT_TO_CORNELIA_TO_BRING_UP                                    = 16760,  -- Ugh. Leave it to Cornelia to bring up the tiniest little matter to those stuffy higher-ups.
        HUME_GALKA_WE_VE_ALL_GOT_DIFFERENT_PERSPECTIVES                         = 16761,  -- Hume...Galka...we've all got different perspectives on things. She of all people should know that.
        DIFFERENT_PERSPECTIVES_YEAH_THAT_MAKES_SENSE_NOT_NECESSARILY            = 16762,  -- Different perspectives... Yeah, that makes sense. Not necessarily. What're you on about?
        SEE_I_KNEW_AN_ADVENTURER_SUCH_AS_YOURSELF                               = 16763,  -- See? I knew an adventurer such as yourself would understand.
        IS_THAT_SO_I_FIGURED_AN_ADVENTURER_SUCH                                 = 16764,  -- Is that so? I figured an adventurer such as yourself would understand.
        OOPS_I_THINK_I_STARTED_IN_THE_MIDDLE                                    = 16765,  -- Oops. I think I started in the middle of the story. Let's see...
        HERE_S_WHAT_HAPPENED_CORNELIA_THINKS_THAT_GALKA                         = 16766,  -- Here's what happened. Cornelia thinks that Galka and Hume should engage in the same type of formal education.
        SHE_BELIEVES_THE_BEST_WAY_TO_BUILD_BRIDGES                              = 16767,  -- She believes the best way to build bridges between our respective groups is to treat everyone equally from childhood.
        IT_S_A_LOFTY_GOAL_I_LL_ADMIT                                            = 16768,  -- It's a lofty goal, I'll admit, but though Galka have never been the type to go to schools as Humes do, we can still do all the things everyone else can. The three Rs, if you will.
        WHEN_OUR_LONG_JOURNEY_OF_REBIRTH_ENDS_WE                                = 16769,  -- When our long journey of rebirth ends, we learn everything we need to know from our elders.
        AND_PERHAPS_THE_BIGGEST_PART_OF_THAT_IS                                 = 16770,  -- And perhaps the biggest part of that is learning what it means to be a Galka.
        GUMBAH_I_DON_T_MEAN_TO_SAY_THAT                                         = 16771,  -- Gumbah, I don't mean to say that there aren't things that young Galka can best learn from their own.
        CORNELIA_I_ASSUME_YOU_WERE_LISTENING_IN                                 = 16772,  -- Cornelia. I assume you were listening in?
        JUST_FROM_THE_END_BUT_IN_THE_SAME                                       = 16773,  -- Just from the end. But in the same way, Galka can learn a lot from Humes, as well.
        AND_SCHOOLS_ARE_MORE_THAN_JUST_PLACES_FOR                               = 16774,  -- And schools are more than just places for our children to read from dusty old manuscripts and memorize their times tables.
        THEY_RE_PLACES_WHERE_CHILDREN_CAN_INTERACT_WITH                         = 16775,  -- They're places where children can interact with others--both their instructors and fellow students--and create the type of special bond that can only come from shared experiences.
        BONDS_HUH_YOU_SURE_THAT_IT_S_NOT                                        = 16776,  -- Bonds, huh? You sure that it's not just a place for people to impress their beliefs on others?
        NO_THAT_S_NOT_WHAT_I_M_SAYING                                           = 16777,  -- No, that's not what I'm saying at all.
        IT_SOUNDS_TO_ME_LIKE_HUMES_TRYING_TO                                    = 16778,  -- It sounds to me like Humes trying to impose their will on the Galka.
        GUMBAH_I_M_NOT_TRYING_TO_DO_ANYTHING                                    = 16779,  -- Gumbah, I'm not trying to do anything of the kind!
        SORRY_CORNELIA_I_SHOULDN_T_HAVE_SNAPPED_AT                              = 16780,  -- ...Sorry, Cornelia. I shouldn't have snapped at you. I've been having some terrible dreams lately, and my lack of good sleep might have caught up with me.
        AND_BESIDES_AFTER_EVERYTHING_THAT_ADVENTURERS_HAVE_DONE                 = 16781,  -- And besides, after everything that adventurers have done for our fair city, I wouldn't want to involve one in some petty squabbles. And surely you didn't come here to trade barbs, either.
        OF_COURSE_NOT_IN_FACT                                                   = 16782,  -- Of course not. In fact...
        I_CAME_WITH_A_REQUEST_OF_SORTS_ONE                                      = 16783,  -- I came with a request of sorts. One of the workers in the Zeruhn Mines came to me with the strangest sighting--a Galkan child wandering aimlessly about the place.
        I_CAN_T_HELP_BUT_THINK_THAT_THE                                         = 16784,  -- I can't help but think that the poor thing might have just been reborn and doesn't know where to go or what to do.
        OF_ALL_THE_THE_ZERUHN_MINES_WE_VE                                       = 16785,  -- Of all the--the Zeruhn mines? We've got to go get some help from the adults!
        I_M_REALLY_WORRIED_MAYBE_I_LL_TREK                                      = 16786,  -- I'm really worried. Maybe I'll trek on ahead.
        CORNELIA_DARN_IT_I_DON_T_THINK_SHE                                      = 16787,  -- Cornelia! Darn it, I don't think she heard me. I know her heart's in the right place, but those mines are dangerous!
        I_THINK_WE_D_BETTER_SPLIT_UP_YOU                                        = 16788,  -- I think we'd better split up. You go after Cornelia while I get some help.
        THE_MINES_AREN_T_EXACTLY_THE_BEST_PLACE                                 = 16789,  -- The mines aren't exactly the best place for someone to wander around unprotected.
        I_LL_HEAD_OVER_AS_SOON_AS_I                                             = 16790,  -- I'll head over as soon as I can. If what Cornelia heard is true, there's a chance you'll run into this Galka before her--so if you do, make sure he's safe, okay?
        HEY_MR_MS_ADVENTURER_WOULD_YOU_MIND_GOING                               = 16791,  -- Hey, Mr./Ms.] Adventurer, would you mind going after Cornelia?
        SHE_S_PROBABLY_GONE_TO_THE_ZERUHN_MINES                                 = 16792,  -- She's probably gone to the Zeruhn mines all on her lonesome.
        I_LL_HEAD_OVER_AS_SOON_AS_I_2                                           = 16793,  -- I'll head over as soon as I can. If what she heard is true, there's a chance you'll run into the newly reborn Galka before Cornelia--so if you do, make sure he's safe, okay?
        AH_WELL_LOOK_WHO_IT_IS_YOU_MUST                                         = 16794,  -- Ah, well look who it is. You must be concerned about the Galkan child too.
        OF_COURSE_I_SHOULD_HAVE_KNOWN_GUMBAH_WOULD                              = 16795,  -- Of course. I should have known Gumbah would worry about me.
        BETWEEN_HIM_AND_THE_FOREMEN_EVERYONE_I_VE                               = 16796,  -- Between him and the foremen, everyone I've talked to today is too concerned for my well-being. They won't even let me further into the mines.
        IT_DOESN_T_MAKE_ANY_SENSE_IF_THEY                                       = 16797,  -- It doesn't make any sense. If they're that insistent on looking after me, then why wouldn't they be twice as interested in the young one wandering around unaccompanied?
        WHEN_I_POINTED_THAT_OUT_RASMUS_SAID_OH                                  = 16798,  -- When I pointed that out, Rasmus said, Oh, right. We did see him further in...
        I_KNOW_THEY_MIGHT_NOT_LET_ME_PROCEED                                    = 16799,  -- I know! They might not let me proceed, but surely they'd have no such qualms about you!
        MAYBE_SOME_OF_THE_OTHER_FOREMEN_WOULD_KNOW                              = 16800,  -- Maybe some of the other foremen would know more. Could you ask them about the Galkan child and go looking for him?
        I_LL_BE_WAITING_FOR_GUMBAH_TO_JOIN                                      = 16801,  -- I'll be waiting for Gumbah to join up. Best of luck.
        CORNELIA_IS_WAITING_FOR_ME_IN_THE_ZERUHN                                = 16802,  -- Cornelia is waiting for me in the Zeruhn Mines?
        THEN_I_GUESS_I_SHOULD_GO_GET_MY                                         = 16803,  -- Then I guess I should go get my things together and head over to meet her. I promise to be quick.
        WHAT_THERE_ACTUALLY_WAS_A_GALKAN_CHILD_IN                               = 16804,  -- What!? There actually was a Galkan child in Zeruhn!?
        I_LL_GET_SOME_GALKAN_ADULTS_AND_RUSH                                    = 16805,  -- I'll get some Galkan adults and rush over there with them! You have to protect the child until we get there!
        THANKS_AGAIN_MR_MS_ADVENTURER_WITHOUT_YOU_WHO                           = 16806,  -- Thanks again, Mr./Ms.] Adventurer. Without you, who knows what that Goblin would have done to him--to Raebrimm.
        HE_S_BEEN_THROUGH_A_LOT_AND_IS                                          = 16807,  -- He's been through a lot, and is resting here in the city. He was scuffed up a little, but we expect him to make a swift, safe recovery.
        STILL_DON_T_YOU_THINK_IT_S_A                                            = 16808,  -- Still, don't you think it's a little out of character, even for a Goblin, to attack a child? What's that all about?
        AH_CORNELIA_WERE_YOU_ABLE_TO_LEARN_ANYTHING                             = 16809,  -- Ah, Cornelia! Were you able to learn anything?
        I_M_AFRAID_I_VE_TURNED_UP_NOTHING                                       = 16810,  -- I'm afraid I've turned up nothing.
        I_ASKED_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_FOR_HELP_AND                             = 16811,  -- I asked the Mythril Musketeers for help, and even though they gladly agreed to look into things, it might take a while before they find out anything concrete.
        I_GUESS_IT_CAN_T_BE_HELPED_BUT                                          = 16812,  -- I guess it can't be helped, but it's still pretty frustrating. The Goblin might come after Raebrimm again, and we've got to be prepared.
        I_AGREE_AND_CAME_UP_WITH_A_PLAN                                         = 16813,  -- I agree, and came up with a plan. What if we were to disguise Raebrimm?
        DISGUISE_HIM                                                            = 16814,  -- Disguise him?
        YEAH_YOU_KNOW_A_LITTLE_WIG_HERE_A                                       = 16815,  -- Yeah. You know, a little wig here, a little makeup there, and no one will be able to tell that it's him!
        AND_IF_THERE_S_ANYONE_WHO_S_AN                                          = 16816,  -- And if there's anyone who's an expert in making disguises to avoid attention, it's me.
        AVOID_ATTENTION_YOU_THE_GUARDS_HAVE_SEEN_THROUGH                        = 16817,  -- Avoid attention? You? The guards have seen through your tricks so many times that I've started to keep a running tally.
        UH_WELL_BE_THAT_AS_IT_MAY                                               = 16818,  -- Uh, well, be that as it may...
        FAILURE_IS_THE_FIRST_STEP_TO_SUCCESS_RIGHT                              = 16819,  -- Failure is the first step to success, right? And I know just the fashionista to help us pull this off.
        HOW_DO_YOU_KNOW_A_FASHIONISTA                                           = 16820,  -- How do you know a fashionista!?
        WHY_EVERYONE_KNOWS_BRYGID_AND_I_THINK_SHE                               = 16821,  -- Why, everyone knows Brygid. And I think she owes me a favor.
        YOU_KNOW_HOW_MUCH_SHE_VALUES_HER_REPUTATION                             = 16822,  -- You know how much she values her reputation. If anyone can help us disguise Raebrimm, it's her.
        WHY_DO_I_HAVE_A_BAD_FEELING_ABOUT                                       = 16823,  -- Why do I have a bad feeling about this?
        I_WOULDN_T_SAY_I_HAVE_A_BAD                                             = 16824,  -- I wouldn't say I have a bad feeling, but there is one small hurdle to climb. She says that she's looking for new entrants in a show that's going to start soon and doesn't have much time to spare for us.
        AND_THAT_S_WHERE_YOU_COME_IN                                            = 16825,  -- And that's where you come in!
        IF_YOU_CAN_HELP_BRYGID_WITH_HER_SHOW                                    = 16826,  -- If you can help Brygid with her show, then she'll absolutely have to assist us! C'mon!
        CORNELIA_CORN_DARN_IT_SHE_RAN_OFF_AGAIN                                 = 16827,  -- Cornelia! Corn-- Darn it, she ran off again. Leave it to her to just assume we'll follow this plan to the letter.
        BUT_I_GUESS_WE_DON_T_HAVE_ANY                                           = 16828,  -- But I guess we don't have any choice now, do we? I know it's an odd request, but think of it as helping to protect an innocent child. Let's go find Brygid.
        I_KNOW_THAT_CORNELIA_S_PLAN_MAY_SOUND                                   = 16829,  -- I know that Cornelia's plan may sound a bit half-baked, but I can't come up with anything better. Let's go find Brygid.
        MR_MS_ADVENTURER_YOU_REMEMBER_OUR_FRIEND_RAEBRIMM                       = 16830,  -- Mr./Ms.] Adventurer, you remember our friend Raebrimm, right? The Galkan child in the unforgettable Goblin getup?
        DO_YOU_REMEMBER_RAEBRIMM_OF_COURSE_WHO_S                                = 16831,  -- Do you remember Raebrimm? Of course. Who's that, again?
        OH_GOOD_I_M_GLAD_TO_HEAR_THAT                                           = 16832,  -- Oh, good. I'm glad to hear that your mind is sound.
        HOW_COULD_YOU_FORGET_AFTER_ALL_YOU_WERE                                 = 16833,  -- How could you forget? After all, you were the one who went to the Zeruhn Mines and saved him from a vicious assault.
        I_VE_GOT_SOME_NEWS_ON_THE_BLACK                                         = 16834,  -- I've got some news on the black-clad Goblin that was threatening him.
        EVIDENTLY_WE_VE_BEEN_ABLE_TO_LEARN_ABOUT                                = 16835,  -- Evidently we've been able to learn about where the menace was headed next.
        CORNELIA_ASKED_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_FOR_THEIR_HELP                    = 16836,  -- Cornelia asked the Mythril Musketeers for their help in tracking the beastman down--and I'm pleased to report that they agreed to aid us.
        GUMBAH_I_M_BACK                                                         = 16837,  -- Gumbah, I'm back!
        OH_AND_LOOK_WHO_S_WITH_YOU                                              = 16838,  -- Oh, and look who's with you!
        YOUR_TIMING_IS_IMPECCABLE_AS_ALWAYS_I_WANTED                            = 16839,  -- %, your timing is impeccable, as always. I wanted to share this with the both of you.
        IRON_EATER_IF_YOU_WOULD                                                 = 16840,  -- Iron Eater, if you would.
        SIGH_HOW_COULD_I_SAY_NO_TO_THAT                                         = 16841,  -- <Sigh> How could I say no to that face?
        WE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_HAVE_WORKED_TIRELESSLY_TO_GATHER                  = 16842,  -- We Mythril Musketeers have worked tirelessly to gather information on your little Goblin problem. While we haven't identified who exactly that little beastie is...
        WE_DO_KNOW_THAT_A_STRANGE_GOBLIN_WAS                                    = 16843,  -- We do know that a strange Goblin was seen flitting about the markets, darting from shadow to shadow in an attempt to avoid detection.
        I_WOULD_IMAGINE_THAT_A_GOBLIN_DRESSED_IN                                = 16844,  -- I would imagine that a Goblin dressed in black from head to toe would arouse some amount of suspicion.
        AYE_AND_SURELY_WE_WOULD_HAVE_HEARD_MORE                                 = 16845,  -- Aye, and surely we would have heard more reports if the beast moved via ordinary means...but his modes of transportation are a bit more arcane, which would explain why he is able to mostly avoid detection in his search for Raebrimm.
        THE_GOOD_NEWS_IS_THAT_BRYGID_S_DISGUISE                                 = 16846,  -- The good news is that Brygid's disguise seems to be working, because Raebrimm remains unharmed.
        IN_FACT_THAT_S_WHY_WE_HAVE_ANY                                          = 16847,  -- In fact, that's why we have any information at all--the Goblin must be getting desperate and resorting to more overt means of tracking his quarry, and just now we got word that someone matching his description was spotted in Korroloka Tunnel.
        THAT_S_GREAT_NEWS                                                       = 16848,  -- That's great news!
        IS_IT_REALLY_I_MEAN_WE_HAVEN_T                                          = 16849,  -- Is it really? I mean, we haven't exactly stopped his advance.
        FEAR_NOT_WE_HAVE_NO_INTENTION_OF_LETTING                                = 16850,  -- Fear not--we have no intention of letting him walk. In fact, I ordered Naji to go after him posthaste.
        AND_BY_WE_I_MEAN_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS                                 = 16851,  -- And by we, I mean the Mythril Musketeers. Miss Cornelia, you are to remain within the city walls.
        YOU_RE_GOING_TO_LET_NAJI_TAKE_THE                                       = 16852,  -- You're going to let Naji take the lead AND make me stay here!?
        NO_WAY_I_VE_GOT_TO_SEE_THIS                                             = 16853,  -- No way. I've got to see this through to its conclusion.
        WHILE_I_SHARE_YOUR_DISTASTE_AT_LETTING_NAJI                             = 16854,  -- While I share your distaste at letting Naji run point...
        HE_IS_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_UNRELIABLE_THOUGH_HE                          = 16855,  -- He is a Mythril Musketeer, unreliable though he may be.
        STILL_I_AGREE_THAT_IT_COULDN_T_HURT                                     = 16856,  -- Still, I agree that it couldn't hurt to send backup of some sort. Adventurer, I'd wager you're more than willing to volunteer.
        WHAT_A_SPLENDID_IDEA                                                    = 16857,  -- What a splendid idea!
        MOST_ASSUREDLY_WE_VE_GOT_TO_LET_RAEBRIMM                                = 16858,  -- Most assuredly. We've got to let Raebrimm know that we will do anything to ensure his safety.
        WE_RE_COUNTING_ON_YOU                                                   = 16859,  -- We're counting on you, %!
        I_KNOW_IT_S_ONLY_KORROLOKA_TUNNEL_BUT                                   = 16860,  -- I know it's only Korroloka Tunnel, but Naji is definitely going to be in over his head.
        WOULD_YOU_MIND_HEADING_OVER_NOT_FOR_MY                                  = 16861,  -- Would you mind heading over? Not for my sake, but for Raebrimm's.
        RAEBRIMM_FILLED_US_IN_ON_WHAT_HAPPENED_YOU                              = 16862,  -- Raebrimm filled us in on what happened. You have my sincere thanks.
        BUT_GLOOM_PHANTOM_EH_WHAT_A_STRAIGHTFORWARD_MONIKER                     = 16863,  -- But Gloom Phantom, eh? What a straightforward moniker.
        AND_THE_THREE_OF_THEM_CALL_THEMSELVES_THE                               = 16864,  -- And the three of them call themselves The Destiny Destroyers. Well, at least their naming sense is on point.
        I_VE_KNOWN_BEASTMEN_TO_BE_A_BIT                                         = 16865,  -- I've known beastmen to be a bit odd, but an egg hunt? Something tells me they don't simply want initial eggs.
        I_HEARD_THAT_EVERYTHING_WENT_WELL                                       = 16866,  -- %! I heard that everything went well.
        YOU_RE_JUST_THE_PERSON_I_WANTED_TO                                      = 16867,  -- You're just the person I wanted to see, too. There's something I don't quite understand.
        CORNELIA_DID_SOMETHING_HAPPEN                                           = 16868,  -- Cornelia? Did something happen?
        WELL_IT_S_ABOUT_NAJI                                                    = 16869,  -- Well, it's about Naji...
        HE_HASN_T_RETURNED_TO_FILE_HIS_REPORT                                   = 16870,  -- He hasn't returned to file his report, and it's well past time for him to make his way back to the city.
        ANY_INFO_ON_NAJI_HE_WENT_AFTER_THE                                      = 16871,  -- Any info on Naji? He went after the three. He wasn't of much use. No clue.
        THE_THREE_YOU_MEAN_THE_GOBLIN_AND_FRIENDS                               = 16872,  -- The three? You mean the Goblin and friends?
        WHILE_HIS_DESIRE_TO_GET_TO_THE_HEART                                    = 16873,  -- While his desire to get to the heart of the matter is commendable, that doesn't change the fact that he left the Galkan child behind.
        NOR_DID_HE_SEND_WORD_BACK_OF_HIS                                        = 16874,  -- Nor did he send word back of his intentions.
        I_HOPE_EVERYTHING_S_OKAY_WHAT_IF_HE                                     = 16875,  -- I hope everything's okay. What if he was hurt? Or captured?
        NO_OTHERS_HAVE_ALREADY_REPORTED_SEEING_HIM_BACK                         = 16876,  -- No, others have already reported seeing him back in the city with no apparent injuries.
        UNTIL_HE_REPORTS_IN_I_SUPPOSE_I_LL                                      = 16877,  -- Until he reports in, I suppose I'll have to ask you, Gumbah, to get the full story from Raebrimm.
        HMMM_ALTHOUGH_I_DID_ORDER_NAJI_TO_TRACK                                 = 16878,  -- Hmmm... Although I did order Naji to track down the source of the problem, he may have gotten in over his head.
        BUT_THE_MOST_CRITICAL_MISSION_ENSURING_RAEBRIMM_S                       = 16879,  -- But the most critical mission--ensuring Raebrimm's safety--appears to have been a rousing success. You have my thanks.
        WE_COULDN_T_HAVE_DONE_IT_WITHOUT_YOU                                    = 16880,  -- We couldn't have done it without you, %.
        GUMBAH_I_D_LIKE_TO_HEAR_WHAT_HAPPENED                                   = 16881,  -- Gumbah, I'd like to hear what happened directly from Raebrimm's mouth. Perhaps we might glean some deeper insight into this matter.
        LEAVE_IT_TO_NAJI_TO_GO_TRAIPSING_OFF                                    = 16882,  -- Leave it to Naji to go traipsing off without backup.
        ACCORDING_TO_RAEBRIMM_THE_GOBLIN_SUCCEEDED_IN_WHATEVER                  = 16883,  -- According to Raebrimm, the Goblin succeeded in...whatever it was that they were trying to do.
        AS_LONG_AS_THEY_LL_LEAVE_HIM_ALONE                                      = 16884,  -- As long as they'll leave him alone, though, does it really matter whether or not they're brought into custody?
        THAT_MAY_VERY_WELL_BE_BUT_I_M                                           = 16885,  -- That may very well be, but I'm afraid we're left with more questions than answers. I'd like to talk to Raebrimm myself.
        OF_COURSE_I_LL_GET_HIM_RIGHT_AWAY                                       = 16886,  -- Of course. I'll get him right away.
        THERE_S_SOMETHING_THAT_S_BEEN_BOTHERING_ME                              = 16887,  -- %, there's something that's been bothering me.
        WHAT_EXACTLY_WAS_THE_DEAL_WITH_THAT_EGG                                 = 16888,  -- What exactly was the deal with that egg...or eggshell, I suppose?
        ANY_IDEA_EGG_SANDWICH_GALKAN_REBIRTH_NO_IDEA                            = 16889,  -- Any idea? Egg...sandwich? Galkan rebirth...? No idea.
        HUH_YOU_THINK_THEY_HAD_A_CASE_OF                                        = 16890,  -- Huh? You think they had a case of the munchies?
        IF_IT_WAS_A_WHOLE_EGG_THEN_I                                            = 16891,  -- If it was a whole egg, then I would understand, but wasn't it just an eggshell?
        THE_JOURNEY_OF_GALKAN_REBIRTH                                           = 16892,  -- The journey of Galkan rebirth...
        I_WISH_I_KNEW_MORE_ABOUT_IT_BUT                                         = 16893,  -- I wish I knew more about it, but Gumbah practically had my hide the last time I asked him about his own journey...
        I_SUPPOSE_YOU_D_RATHER_NOT_TALK_ABOUT                                   = 16894,  -- I suppose you'd rather not talk about it.
        MAYBE_YOU_THINK_I_M_JUST_SOME_GIRL                                      = 16895,  -- Maybe you think I'm just some girl in over my head, like everyone else...
        CORNELIA_THE_CONCLUSION_WE_CAME_TO_IS_THAT                              = 16896,  -- Cornelia, the conclusion we came to is that the Goblin wasn't after the eggshell itself, but rather a whole egg.
        THEY_WERE_TRAILING_RAEBRIMM_BECAUSE_THEY_CAUGHT_THE                     = 16897,  -- They were trailing Raebrimm because they caught the scent of it, but what they found was just a shell of what they thought it would be.
        THAT_S_THE_LAMEST_PUN_I_VE_EVER                                         = 16898,  -- That's the lamest pun I've ever heard.
        I_COULDN_T_RESIST_PERHAPS_THAT_MYSTERY_WILL                             = 16899,  -- I couldn't resist. Perhaps that mystery will have to wait for later, and we'll have to content ourselves with Raebrimm's freedom.
        YOU_RE_RIGHT                                                            = 16900,  -- You're right.
        WE_LL_LET_YOU_KNOW_IF_WE_HEAR                                           = 16901,  -- %, we'll let you know if we hear anything else.
        AS_WILL_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_NAJI_S_HEART                             = 16902,  -- As will the Mythril Musketeers. Naji's heart is in the right place.
        I_D_LIKE_TO_GIVE_YOU_SOMETHING_OTHER                                    = 16903,  -- I'd like to give you something other than just platitudes for your efforts.
        ME_TOO_IT_S_A_SPECIAL_RECIPE_FAVORED                                    = 16904,  -- Me too. It's a special recipe favored by my extended family.
        UNTIL_NEXT_TIME                                                         = 16905,  -- Until next time!
        YOUR_HELP_WAS_CRITICAL_IN_ENSURING_RAEBRIMM_S                           = 16906,  -- Your help was critical in ensuring Raebrimm's safety. Here's a little something from me and Cornelia.
        THIS_IS_AN_EXPLANATION_OF_THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL                            = 16907,  -- This is an explanation of the Assist Channel feature, which allows new and returning players to seek help from veteran adventurers.
        YOU_MUST_TAKE_ON_THE_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE                                = 16908,  -- You must take on the % Records of Eminence objective before receiving the explanation.
        YOU_MUST_COMPLETE_BEFORE_TAKING_ON_THE_RECORDS                          = 16909,  -- You must complete % before taking on the % Records of Eminence objective.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_LEARN_ABOUT_WHAT                                    = 16910,  -- What do you want to learn about? What is the Assist Channel? How can I post a message? What are the requirements? Where can I access it? Tell me about mentor messages. Where can I find mentors? What are Thumbs Up and Warnings? What happens if I am muted? When do my posting rights expire? Nothing for now.
        THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL_IS_A_SPECIAL_CHAT_CHANNEL                            = 16911,  -- The Assist Channel is a special chat channel that allows adventurers to ask questions and receive advice from veteran players known as mentors.
        PRESS_THE_SPACE_BAR_TO_BRING_UP_THE                                     = 16912,  -- Press the space bar to bring up the text window at the bottom of the screen and type /assistj (your message) or /assiste (your message) to post your message.
        YOU_CAN_ALSO_USE_AJ_FOR_ASSISTJ_AND                                     = 16913,  -- You can also use /aj for /assistj, and /ae for /assiste.
        ADDITIONALLY_PRESSING_CTRL_Q_WILL_DISPLAY_ASSISTJ_OR                    = 16914,  -- Additionally, pressing CTRL+Q will display /assistj or /assiste in the text window for you.
        YOU_CAN_CHANGE_THE_CTRL_Q_SHORTCUT_COMMAND                              = 16915,  -- You can change the CTRL+Q shortcut command...
        BY_GOING_TO_MAIN_MENU_CONFIG_MISC_2                                     = 16916,  -- ...by going to Main Menu > Config > Misc. 2 > Key Assignment > Commands > Chat: /AssistE or /AssistJ.
        IT_IS_RECOMMENDED_THAT_YOU_USE_ASSISTJ_AJ                               = 16917,  -- It is recommended that you use /assistj (/aj) when posting in Japanese, and /assiste (/ae) when posting in English.
        YOU_MUST_MEET_ONE_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_CONDITIONS                           = 16918,  -- You must meet one of the following conditions in order to post to the Assist Channel.
        ID_1_YOU_ARE_A_NEW_PLAYER_YOU_MAY                                       = 16919,  -- 1. You are a new player You may post messages from the moment you first set foot in Vana'diel.
        ID_2_YOU_ARE_A_RETURNEE_AS_A_RETURNING                                  = 16920,  -- 2. You are a returnee As a returning player, you may post messages upon logging in with a character that has not logged in for at least 48 days.
        ID_3_YOU_ARE_A_MENTOR_YOU_MAY_POST                                      = 16921,  -- 3. You are a mentor You may post messages as long as you remain a mentor to other players.
        NEW_PLAYERS_AND_RETURNEES_MAY_POST_MESSAGES_UNTIL                       = 16922,  -- New players and returnees may post messages until they have been logged in for a total of 48 hours since first receiving their posting rights.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_CHECK_HOW_LONG_YOU                                       = 16923,  -- If you wish to check how long you can continue to post for, speak to an and choose "When do my posting rights expire?" to see how much time you have left.
        THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL_CAN_ONLY_BE_USED_IN                                  = 16924,  -- The Assist Channel can only be used in the following areas.
        AVAILABLE_AREAS                                                         = 16925,  -- Available areas: %, %, %, %, %, %...
        ID_16926                                                                = 16926,  -- ...%, %, %, %, %, %, %, %...
        ID_16927                                                                = 16927,  -- ...%, %, %, %, %, %, %, %...
        AND_YOUR_MOG_HOUSE_RENT_A_ROOM                                          = 16928,  -- ...%, %, %, and your Mog House (Rent-a-Room).
        YOU_CANNOT_POST_OR_READ_MESSAGES_OUTSIDE_OF                             = 16929,  -- You cannot post or read messages outside of the areas listed above.
        EVEN_IN_AREAS_WHERE_MESSAGES_ARE_ALLOWED_YOU                            = 16930,  -- Even in areas where messages are allowed, you cannot post consecutive messages. Please wait a while after posting a message.
        MENTOR_MESSAGES_ARE_ACCOMPANIED_BY_A_FLAG_O                             = 16931,  -- Mentor messages are accompanied by a flag (o/) marker. This marker indicates the mentor's reliability (Mentor Class) and experience as an adventurer (Mastery Rank).
        AS_A_MENTOR_S_MENTOR_CLASS_INCREASES_THE                                = 16932,  -- As a mentor's Mentor Class increases, the color and shape of the marker will change: o/ > o9 > oC
        A_OC_MARKER_IS_A_SIGN_THAT_THE                                          = 16933,  -- A oC marker is a sign that the mentor has earned the highest levels of trust from other adventurers.
        THE_NUMBER_AFFIXED_TO_THE_MARKER_IS_THE                                 = 16934,  -- The number affixed to the marker is the mentor's Mastery Rank, and indicates how experienced the mentor is as an adventurer.
        THE_HIGHER_THE_NUMBER_THE_MORE_EXPERIENCED_THE                          = 16935,  -- The higher the number, the more experienced the mentor is.
        YOU_CAN_CHECK_YOUR_OWN_MASTERY_RANK_EVEN                                = 16936,  -- You can check your own Mastery Rank even if you do not serve as a mentor, so feel free to take a look every now and then if you are curious.
        YOU_CAN_CHECK_YOUR_MASTERY_RANK_BY_GOING                                = 16937,  -- You can check your Mastery Rank by going to Main Menu > Status > Profile.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_SPEAK_DIRECTLY_TO_A                                      = 16938,  -- If you wish to speak directly to a mentor, you can search for mentors by going to Main Menu > Help Desk > Mentor Search.
        THE_THUMBS_UP_FEATURE_ENABLES_YOU_TO_LET                                = 16939,  -- The Thumbs Up feature enables you to let mentors know when their comments proved to be especially helpful.
        MENTORS_WHO_EARN_LOTS_OF_THUMBS_UP_REPLIES                              = 16940,  -- Mentors who earn lots of Thumbs Up replies from other adventurers will see their Mentor Class increase.
        REMEMBER_TO_GIVE_A_THUMBS_UP_TO_ANY                                     = 16941,  -- Remember to give a Thumbs Up to any mentor you feel helped you out or taught you something useful.
        A_WARNING_IS_A_FEATURE_THAT_CAN_ONLY                                    = 16942,  -- A Warning is a feature that can only be used by mentors.
        PLEASE_USE_THIS_FEATURE_WHEN_A_POST_S                                   = 16943,  -- Please use this feature when a post's contents are insufficient or otherwise may be construed as harassment.
        TO_SEND_A_THUMBS_UP_OR_WARNING_TO                                       = 16944,  -- To send a Thumbs Up or Warning to another player, open the Chat Log Window and move the cursor over the relevant message and press the confirm button (Enter key) to bring up the evaluation menu.
        EVALUATIONS_CAN_BE_MADE_FOR_10_MINUTES_FOLLOWING                        = 16945,  -- Evaluations can be made for 10 minutes following the designated player's latest post to the Assist Channel.
        YOU_MAY_SEND_UP_TO_ONE_THUMBS_UP                                        = 16946,  -- You may send up to one Thumbs Up and one Warning per day (Earth time).
        THE_MUTE_FEATURE_PLACES_RESTRICTIONS_ON_YOUR_ABILITY                    = 16947,  -- The Mute feature places restrictions on your ability to post, meaning that other players will be unable to see the messages you post to the Assist Channel.
        PLEASE_REFRAIN_FROM_POSTING_UNSUITABLE_CONTENT_SO_THAT                  = 16948,  -- Please refrain from posting unsuitable content so that the veteran adventurers are not forced to mute you.
        MUTE_STATUS_CAN_BE_REMOVED_BY_PLAYERS_THAT                              = 16949,  -- Mute status can be removed by players that have the necessary Mute List access rights, or it will be removed automatically 24 hours (Earth time) after the mute status was enabled.
        YOU_ARE_FREE_TO_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE                                    = 16950,  -- You are free to post messages to the Assist Channel until you decide to stop serving as a mentor.
        YOU_MAY_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL                             = 16951,  -- You may post messages to the Assist Channel until : on //. (Time remaining: Approx. # [sec./min./hr.])
        IF_YOU_LOG_OUT_WHILE_YOU_STILL_HAVE                                     = 16952,  -- If you log out while you still have time available, your remaining time will be carried over to the next time you log in.
        YOU_ARE_ABOUT_TO_LOSE_THE_ABILITY_TO                                    = 16953,  -- You are about to lose the ability to post messages to the Assist Channel.
        YOU_ARE_UNABLE_TO_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE                                  = 16954,  -- You are unable to post messages to the Assist Channel.
        TAKE_ON_THE_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_OBJECTIVE_FROM                          = 16955,  -- Take on the % Records of Eminence objective from the Tutorial section of the Records of Eminence Menu and speak to the A.M.A.N. liaison.
        FAIR_GREETINGS_TO_YOU_WANDERER_I_AM_A                                   = 16956,  -- Fair greetings to you, wanderer. I am a linkshell concierge, charged with uniting lone explorers of Vana'diel with linkshells of similar goals.
        HOW_MAY_I_HELP_YOU_TODAY                                                = 16957,  -- How may I help you today?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_DESIRE_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_SHOW                                 = 16958,  -- What do you desire? Nothing for now. Show me recruiting linkshells. I'd like to hand out %. Tell me more. Open up the linkshell window.
        IT_WAS_MY_PLEASURE_TO_MEET_WITH_YOU                                     = 16959,  -- It was my pleasure to meet with you this fine day. May you encounter many friendly faces throughout your travels.
        EXCELLENT_PLEASE_SELECT_WHICH_LINKSHELL_YOU_ARE_INTERESTED              = 16960,  -- Excellent. Please select which linkshell you are interested in contacting.
        ARE_YOU_CERTAIN                                                         = 16961,  -- Are you certain?
        REALLY_RECEIVE_THE_LINKPEARL_OF_COURSE_NO_THANK                         = 16962,  -- Really receive the linkpearl? Of course. No, thank you.
        IN_THE_INTEREST_OF_FAIRNESS_I_AM_UNABLE                                 = 16963,  -- In the interest of fairness, I am unable to distribute multiple linkpearls to someone on the same day. Please come back tomorrow.
        IT_IS_MY_SINCERE_PLEASURE_TO_BESTOW_THIS                                = 16964,  -- It is my sincere pleasure to bestow this upon you.
        YOUR_NEW_LINKSHELL_IS_BEYOND_DOUBT_FILLED_WITH                          = 16965,  -- Your new linkshell is beyond doubt filled with many looking for new companions. Be sure to say a few words of greeting.
        I_HAVE_PREPARED_A_SMALL_MANUAL_DESCRIBING_THE                           = 16966,  -- I have prepared a small manual describing the importance of treating others with respect. Please have a quick glance at it when you have a moment.
        MAY_YOUR_NEW_LINKSHELL_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH_FOND                            = 16967,  -- May your new linkshell provide you with fond memories that will last a lifetime.
        THOUGH_IT_PAINS_ME_TO_SAY_THIS_I                                        = 16968,  -- Though it pains me to say this, I have no % that meet your requirements at this time.
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_I_CAN_CANCEL_YOUR_REGISTRATION                        = 16969,  -- Should you desire, I can cancel your registration.
        CANCEL_REGISTRATION_YES_PLEASE_NOT_AT_THIS_TIME                         = 16970,  -- Cancel registration? Yes, please. Not at this time.
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_TO_LOOK_FOR_MEMBERS_I                                 = 16971,  -- Should you desire to look for members, I can distribute % in your stead by utilizing the energies continued within your equipped %.
        DURING_THE_PROCESS_PLEASE_EQUIP_EITHER_OR_AS                            = 16972,  -- During the process, please equip either % or % as Linkshell 1 and select I'd like to hand out %.
        ONE_THAT_STEP_HAS_BEEN_COMPLETED_I_WILL                                 = 16973,  -- One that step has been completed, I will ask you a series of questions.
        TO_CANCEL_YOUR_REGISTRATION_EQUIP_OR_AS_LINKSHELL                       = 16974,  -- To cancel your registration, equip % or % as Linkshell 1, speak to me again, and select the appropriate linkshell from the list.
        UNFORTUNATELY_ONLY_THOSE_EQUIPPED_WITH_OR_AS_LINKSHELL                  = 16975,  -- Unfortunately, only those equipped with % or % as Linkshell 1 are able to distribute %.
        ONCE_IN_A_LIFETIME_MEETINGS_MAKE_FOR_WONDERFUL                          = 16976,  -- Once-in-a-lifetime meetings make for wonderful stories, but no treasure can compare to being part of a group of friends you can call home.
        LINKSHELL_CONCIERGES_SUCH_AS_MYSELF_BRING_TOGETHER_ADVENTURERS          = 16977,  -- Linkshell concierges such as myself bring together adventurers of similar interests.
        IN_A_WORD_WE_MATCH_ADVENTURERS_LOOKING_FOR                              = 16978,  -- In a word, we match adventurers looking for linkshells with those linkshells interested in taking in new members.
        I_ACCEPT_FROM_LINKSHELLS_THE_WORLD_OVER_AND                             = 16979,  -- I accept % from linkshells the world over and distribute them to appropriate adventurers.
        THIS_SERVICE_IS_PROVIDED_BY_THE_ADVENTURERS_MUTUAL                      = 16980,  -- This service is provided by the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network, and as such, anyone working for Vana'diel's greater good is eligible to participate.
        ADDITIONALLY_PLEASE_BE_AWARE_THAT_I_AM_ONLY                             = 16981,  -- Additionally, please be aware that I am only able to offer you one % per day.
        THOUGH_WE_WOULD_LIKE_TO_OFFER_THIS_SERVICE                              = 16982,  -- Though we would like to offer this service free of charge, the network has its own expenses that must be paid, so we charge a nominal fee of # gil at the time of registration.
        IT_IS_ALSO_WORTH_NOTING_THAT_CAN_ONLY                                   = 16983,  -- It is also worth noting that % can only be registered by adventurers who have been active in Vana'diel for at least # days (Earth time).
        IT_IS_WORTH_NOTING_THAT_EACH_CONCIERGE_MAY                              = 16984,  -- It is worth noting that each concierge may only register a maximum of # linkshells.
        ONCE_THE_NUMBER_OF_REGISTRATIONS_HAS_HIT_THE                            = 16985,  -- Once the number of registrations has hit the limit, existing registrations will be canceled in order of oldest to newest.
        SERVER_MAINTENANCES_WILL_ALSO_IMMEDIATELY_CANCEL_ALL_REGISTRATIONS      = 16986,  -- Server maintenances will also immediately cancel all registrations, so be sure to keep your information up-to-date.
        THANK_YOU_FOR_TAKING_THE_TIME_TO_USE                                    = 16987,  -- Thank you for taking the time to use our service. Let me confirm the information contained within.
        CORRECT                                                                 = 16988,  -- , correct?
        LS0                                                                     = 16989,  -- LS0: .
        LS1                                                                     = 16990,  -- LS1: .
        LS0_NO_SENDING                                                          = 16991,  -- LS0: (No sending).
        LS1_NO_SENDING                                                          = 16992,  -- LS1: (No sending).
        SHALL_I_START_LOOKING_FOR_NEW_MEMBERS_FOR                               = 16993,  -- Shall I start looking for new members for a fee of # gil?
        LOOK_FOR_NEW_MEMBERS_GIL_THAT_SOUNDS_WONDERFUL                          = 16994,  -- Look for new members? (# gil) That sounds wonderful. I'd rather not.
        I_M_QUITE_SORRY_TO_HEAR_YOU_DECLINE                                     = 16995,  -- I'm quite sorry to hear you decline. Please let me know if you change your mind.
        I_WILL_NOW_ASK_YOU_A_SERIES_OF                                          = 16996,  -- I will now ask you a series of questions about your preferences. Be sure to answer truthfully so that you can find new members that match your style.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_LANGUAGE_PREFERENCE_JAPANESE_ENGLISH_OTHER                 = 16997,  -- What is your language preference? Japanese. English. Other. Back.
        WHAT_DAYS_ARE_YOU_MOST_ACTIVE_EVERY_DAY                                 = 16998,  -- What days are you most active? Every day. Weekends and holidays. Weekdays. Monday. Tuesday. Wednesday. Thursday. Friday. Saturday. Sunday. Back.
        WHAT_DAYS_ARE_YOU_MOST_ACTIVE_NO_DAY                                    = 16999,  -- What days are you most active? [-/Z]No day set. [-/Z]Mondays. [-/Z]Tuesdays. [-/Z]Wednesdays. [-/Z]Thursdays. [-/Z]Fridays. [-/Z]Saturdays. [-/Z]Sundays. [-/Z]Holidays. Back. Next. Update.
        WHEN_DO_YOU_PLAYING_ON_NO_TIME_SET                                      = 17000,  -- When do you [start/stop] playing on [weekdays/weekends]? No time set. 12:00 a.m. 1:00 a.m.:00 a.m.:00 a.m. 4:00 a.m. 5:00 a.m. 6:00 a.m. 7:00 a.m. 8:00 a.m. 9:00 a.m. 10:00 a.m. 11:00 a.m. 12:00 p.m. 1:00 p.m.:00 p.m.:00 p.m. 4:00 p.m. 5:00 p.m. 6:00 p.m. 7:00 p.m. 8:00 p.m. 9:00 p.m. 10:00 p.m. 11:00 p.m. Back.
        DESIGNATE_A_TIME_ZONE_NO_DESIGNATION_JAPANESE_STANDARD                  = 17001,  -- Designate a time zone. No designation. Japanese Standard Time (JST). Pacific Time (PST|PDT). Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). Back.
        WHAT_TIME_ARE_YOU_ACTIVE_JST_IN_THE                                     = 17002,  -- What time are you active? (JST) In the morning. In the afternoon. In the evening. At night. In the wee hours of the morning. Return to previous selection.
